{"term":"1966","caseName":"Miller v. Pate","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1966/250","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - January 12, 1967","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren13/oral_argument_audio/14911","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Petitioner versus Frank J. Pate, Warden.","start":0,"stop":4.065,"duration":4.07},{"text":"Mr. Lassers, you may continue your argument.","start":4.065,"stop":7.869,"duration":3.8}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":7.869,"stop":12.629,"duration":4.76},{"text":"At the habeas corpus hearing before Judge Perry, the -- we produced evidence regarding a pair of jockey shorts.","start":12.629,"stop":22.693,"duration":10.06},{"text":"These shorts were originally introduced with the 1956 trial and at that time it was evidence from Mr. Litterly that I mentioned yesterday that these shorts have Type A blood on them and there was some out there evidence which we question that that the little girl who was murdered also had Type A blood and these shorts according to the prosecution theory had been worn by the petitioner and had been abandoned by him in his flight.","start":22.693,"stop":52.962,"duration":30.27},{"text":"We pre --","start":52.962,"stop":53.125,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask?","start":53.125,"stop":54.074,"duration":0.95},{"text":"How did the testimony of the little girl who had Type A blood get into the case?","start":54.074,"stop":61.356,"duration":7.28}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The mother was -- testified to that effect.","start":61.356,"stop":65.653,"duration":4.3},{"text":"It was a hearsay testimony as far as she was concerned but it got into the record.","start":65.653,"stop":71.079,"duration":5.43}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You say, she did not testify --","start":71.079,"stop":72.488,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"She did.","start":72.488,"stop":73.39,"duration":0.9},{"text":"The mother of the little girl testified, Your Honor.","start":73.39,"stop":76.449,"duration":3.06}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in shape that --","start":76.449,"stop":77.777,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"In shape, yes, correct.","start":77.777,"stop":80.514,"duration":2.74}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Based upon what did she say?","start":80.514,"stop":82.836,"duration":2.32}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"She didn't say.","start":82.836,"stop":85.026,"duration":2.19},{"text":"It was fudge.","start":85.026,"stop":86.038,"duration":1.01},{"text":"It appeared as though she was based at a school record tied in with the child's weight.","start":86.038,"stop":91.828,"duration":5.79},{"text":"But she made the statement that she had a Type A blood and that's all the evidence there was at the trial as to the little girl's blood type.","start":91.828,"stop":100.052,"duration":8.22}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there any question about the accuracy of the statement?","start":100.052,"stop":103.099,"duration":3.05}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we -- we think it was hearsay evidence, Mr. Justice Black.","start":103.099,"stop":106.733,"duration":3.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that it was hearsay --","start":106.733,"stop":108.136,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":108.136,"stop":109.257,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- but it was in without objection.","start":109.257,"stop":110.434,"duration":1.18}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well --","start":110.434,"stop":111.224,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there any question about the accuracy?","start":111.224,"stop":112.987,"duration":1.76}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We have no way of knowing positively because the child is dead.","start":112.987,"stop":119.57,"duration":6.58},{"text":"So we can't verify one way or the other.","start":119.57,"stop":121.557,"duration":1.99}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Have you made any efforts to find out?","start":121.557,"stop":123.578,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We have made efforts inconclusive.","start":123.578,"stop":127.906,"duration":4.33}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Asked a doctor?","start":127.906,"stop":129.747,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry.","start":129.747,"stop":130.417,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you ask a doctor?","start":130.417,"stop":133.149,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, we made various inquiries at the hospital and so forth.","start":133.149,"stop":138.264,"duration":5.12},{"text":"They turned up some slips which showed Type A blood but the exact timing and dates and it was very confused.","start":138.264,"stop":148.895,"duration":10.63},{"text":"We couldn't establish it either way.","start":148.895,"stop":150.06,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So did they had the Type A blood but it didn't show the time that she had it, is that it?","start":150.06,"stop":154.862,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't remember the details whether the slip was undated or what the problem was but I remember that we couldn't establish it either way.","start":154.862,"stop":165.282,"duration":10.42},{"text":"Now --","start":165.282,"stop":166.05,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose if she had the type of blood any time she would always have it.","start":166.05,"stop":170.421,"duration":4.37}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is -- it's my understanding that that is correct, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":170.421,"stop":174.534,"duration":4.11},{"text":"Now, at the District Court hearing, for the first time, Judge Perry permitted us to have a scientific examination made of the shorts and at that time, we produced evidence showing that the shorts were saturated not with blood but they were saturated with paint.","start":174.534,"stop":194.903,"duration":20.37},{"text":"Now, we've actually brought up the shorts up here, they look terrible Your Honors and they -- all what you see here is paint and not blood.","start":194.903,"stop":207.753,"duration":12.85},{"text":"Now --","start":207.753,"stop":208.474,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how do you tell by looking at it that's paint and not blood?","start":208.474,"stop":211.556,"duration":3.08}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We cannot Your Honor, Mr. Justice Black, no.","start":211.556,"stop":215.092,"duration":3.54},{"text":"It took us --","start":215.092,"stop":215.753,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any blood?","start":215.753,"stop":216.844,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"What?","start":216.844,"stop":217.279,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any blood in the shorts?","start":217.279,"stop":218.336,"duration":1.06}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is a disputed fact.","start":218.336,"stop":220.835,"duration":2.5},{"text":"Now, our chemist testified that he could find no evidence of blood.","start":220.835,"stop":227.613,"duration":6.78},{"text":"He made this test in December of '63.","start":227.613,"stop":230.739,"duration":3.13},{"text":"Now, there was testimony back in '56 by the state witness Litterly that he found blood on the shorts.","start":230.739,"stop":238.772,"duration":8.03},{"text":"But our man couldn't find any in '63.","start":238.772,"stop":243.183,"duration":4.41},{"text":"Now --","start":243.183,"stop":243.912,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they find any in '63?","start":243.912,"stop":247.3,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The state?","start":247.3,"stop":247.926,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"The state, yes.","start":247.926,"stop":249.55,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The state didn't make any new test in '63 one way or the other.","start":249.55,"stop":254.674,"duration":5.12},{"text":"Now --","start":254.674,"stop":255.632,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"How obvious is that -- is the red part of it that you attribute to paint than they attribute to blood on the shorts?","start":255.632,"stop":265.358,"duration":9.73}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn't hear your question.","start":265.358,"stop":266.507,"duration":1.15}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"How obvious is the paint on the shorts that --","start":266.507,"stop":270.592,"duration":4.08}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, this was always referred to at the 1956 trial as the blood stained shorts even petitioner so referred to it and Litterly, in the '56 testimony said, he talked about -- he said that the red -- the staining material on the shorts were -- was blood.","start":270.592,"stop":290.809,"duration":20.22}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, as repulsive as it maybe, would you open it up so I can see it?","start":290.809,"stop":294.159,"duration":3.35}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly.","start":294.159,"stop":296.993,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, is there any question about it that what everything we can see there is paint.","start":296.993,"stop":303.919,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think there is any question, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":303.919,"stop":306.1,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"So the state contends that anything that can be seen on there now is blood.","start":306.1,"stop":310.952,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They have not challenged that.","start":310.952,"stop":312.685,"duration":1.73},{"text":"All that they can claim was that there was -- that their testimony -- that their expert in '56, said that there was blood but I think it is undisputed now that everything that Your Honors see is paint.","start":312.685,"stop":326.645,"duration":13.96}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but didn't the counsel for the petitioner at the original trial in 1956 see those shorts?","start":326.645,"stop":338.048,"duration":11.4}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes he did, Mr. Justice Fortas.","start":338.048,"stop":340.323,"duration":2.27}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And what did he do after he saw them?","start":340.323,"stop":344.263,"duration":3.94}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well --","start":344.263,"stop":344.284,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he have an analysis made of them?","start":344.284,"stop":346.13,"duration":1.85},{"text":"Did he ask --?","start":346.13,"stop":347.38,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He moved the Court to have a scientific examination made of the shorts and it was denied.","start":347.38,"stop":355.178,"duration":7.8},{"text":"So he couldn't present --","start":355.178,"stop":355.734,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you mean he moved the Court to have a scientific examination made?","start":355.734,"stop":358.829,"duration":3.1},{"text":"Did he move --","start":358.829,"stop":358.865,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He presented a motion.","start":358.865,"stop":360.807,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he move -- did he move that he'd be allowed to have an expert examine the shorts?","start":360.807,"stop":367.911,"duration":7.1}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":367.911,"stop":369.105,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And that was denied?","start":369.105,"stop":370.484,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was denied.","start":370.484,"stop":371.874,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, had he had an opportunity and have such scientific examination made prior to trial?","start":371.874,"stop":378.832,"duration":6.96}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He moved it in May that it was an examination to examine all the physical evidence, to have a scientific examination made.","start":378.832,"stop":385.743,"duration":6.91},{"text":"It was made in May and the trial was held in September.","start":385.743,"stop":390.206,"duration":4.46}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"So that -- and that was denied in May.","start":390.206,"stop":392.854,"duration":2.65}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was denied.","start":392.854,"stop":393.707,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"So that your point about the subsequent District Court hearing in 1961 or whenever it was.","start":393.707,"stop":401.838,"duration":8.13}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"'63.","start":401.838,"stop":402.804,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"'63.","start":402.804,"stop":404.692,"duration":1.89},{"text":"Is merely that it's a dramatic demonstration of the fact that this was a prejudicial error.","start":404.692,"stop":412.129,"duration":7.44}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, Your Honor.","start":412.129,"stop":413.939,"duration":1.81},{"text":"Yes.","start":413.939,"stop":414.724,"duration":0.78}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there motion made directly and specifically to the judge, stating that this was not blood but was paint?","start":414.724,"stop":422.71,"duration":7.99}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":422.71,"stop":423.607,"duration":0.9},{"text":"No, Mr. Justice Black, it was not.","start":423.607,"stop":427.665,"duration":4.06},{"text":"There was no way to tell as I understand it by looking at this, what this stating material is.","start":427.665,"stop":434.585,"duration":6.92}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But what do you mean when you say that he made a motion?","start":434.585,"stop":437.575,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He made a motion to have a scientific examination made of all of the physical evidence in the case.","start":437.575,"stop":443.436,"duration":5.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That they have to have a scientific investigation there.","start":443.436,"stop":445.632,"duration":2.2},{"text":"What kind of scientific --","start":445.632,"stop":447.138,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not specified.","start":447.138,"stop":447.639,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of all the evidence in the case.","start":447.639,"stop":448.989,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was -- of all the physical evidence.","start":448.989,"stop":451.363,"duration":2.37},{"text":"It was not specified and there was a --","start":451.363,"stop":457.609,"duration":6.25}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there any question amongst as to where these pants were in '56 to '63?","start":457.609,"stop":464.606,"duration":7}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They were in the hands of the prosecution up to the time of the trial and then they were in the -- I believe in the possession of the trial court.","start":464.606,"stop":473.888,"duration":9.28},{"text":"I'm not certain of that.","start":473.888,"stop":474.572,"duration":0.68},{"text":"And then they were transmitted to the Supreme Court of Illinois and we got them into the hands of the District Court from the Supreme Court of Illinois and then they went to the Court of Appeals and then they came to this Court.","start":474.572,"stop":488.596,"duration":14.02},{"text":"Now, the -- there are two other errors Your Honors that we feel are critical here.","start":488.596,"stop":496.564,"duration":7.97},{"text":"One relates to the state's star witness, Betty Baldwin who is now Betty Baldwin-Curry who testified that on the night of the murder that this -- that the petitioner admitted the crime to her in the course of a taxi ride, he was a taxi driver and in 1963, before Judge Perry, she recanted her testimony and denied that she had ever -- that he had ever made such a statement to her.","start":496.564,"stop":527.532,"duration":30.97}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Did his confession make any reference to having admitted the crime to her?","start":527.532,"stop":533.173,"duration":5.64}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't -- no, I don't believe it did.","start":533.173,"stop":535.384,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought it had.","start":535.384,"stop":537.219,"duration":1.84}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It did?","start":537.219,"stop":540.028,"duration":2.81},{"text":"Mr. Rosenfield says that it does make such a reference.","start":540.028,"stop":545.544,"duration":5.52},{"text":"Now, at the '63 trial, again by discovery, we learned for the first time of a statement in the prosecution files given by this woman very shortly after the crime.","start":545.544,"stop":559.017,"duration":13.47},{"text":"At the '56 trial, she was asked how long she had known the petitioner and her answer was two years.","start":559.017,"stop":567.246,"duration":8.23},{"text":"And at the 19 -- and the statement that she gave to the prosecution right after the crime was that she had known him for five weeks.","start":567.246,"stop":577.434,"duration":10.19},{"text":"Now, that was first learned by us in 1963.","start":577.434,"stop":582.398,"duration":4.96},{"text":"Then there was a whole long list of other facts known to the prosecution prior to the ‘56 trial which cast serious doubt on the reliability and trustworthiness of this witness.","start":582.398,"stop":597.921,"duration":15.52}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What was the time relevance here or importance of the length of time she had known him?","start":597.921,"stop":604.459,"duration":6.54}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Because if she had known him for two years, Mr. Justice Black then if she conveyed the impression -- conveyed the impression to the jury that it was the -- that there was the kind of relationship between them that if he had committed a crime that he would admit it to her whereas if it was only five weeks, it would be less likely that he would make such an admission to somebody that he had just knew very briefly.","start":604.459,"stop":634.511,"duration":30.05},{"text":"Now, the -- my time has expired, Your Honors and I want to save some time for rebuttal.","start":634.511,"stop":646.149,"duration":11.64},{"text":"We're not going to -- because I have mentioned that I don't want the Court of Appeals that we think that they're unimportant but there were serious questions with regard to being cut off in the examination of a key defense witness Mrs. Alice Baxter who is the landlady.","start":646.149,"stop":664.6,"duration":18.45},{"text":"And the landlady came up to the 1963 trial and said that he was in his room in her house at the time that the crime took place.","start":664.6,"stop":677.451,"duration":12.85},{"text":"In '56, before the trial, the defense counsel tried to interview this witness.","start":677.451,"stop":684.016,"duration":6.56},{"text":"She spoke to him once or twice and then the -- then she called the prosecution and the prosecution told her that she has a constitutional right not to talk to the defense counsel and then she refused to talk to him any further.","start":684.016,"stop":702.289,"duration":18.27},{"text":"So she was listed as a prosecution witness in 1956.","start":702.289,"stop":708.615,"duration":6.33},{"text":"She was not called by the defense in '63, as I said, she came forward and she said that he was in her house at the time of crime.","start":708.615,"stop":717.065,"duration":8.45}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright, are you or somebody on your side going to deal with the claim that the -- confession itself is coerced?","start":717.065,"stop":726.595,"duration":9.53}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I intended to deal with that Your Honor but my time is going down except for the fact that there was a lie about the hair plus the fact that the prosecution told -- he asked to see his parents and the police told him, “You can't see your parents.","start":726.595,"stop":745.698,"duration":19.1},{"text":"Your parents don't want to have anything more to do with you.”","start":745.698,"stop":748.458,"duration":2.76},{"text":"And all the time the parents were out trying to find out where he was in lining up an attorney.","start":748.458,"stop":754.978,"duration":6.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand -- I understand, Mr. Lassers that the defense tried to call this lady, Mrs. Baxter at the trial, is that correct?","start":754.978,"stop":766.418,"duration":11.44}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":766.418,"stop":767.241,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And they tried to -- because they couldn't talk to her after the prosecution had told her that she had a constitutional right not to talk to him.","start":767.241,"stop":778.058,"duration":10.82},{"text":"They asked the Court to let them examine her as a court witness.","start":778.058,"stop":782.696,"duration":4.64}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is right, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":782.696,"stop":783.19,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"The prosecution said that they would only do that if the defense admitted her unreliability and the Court on that objection refuse let her be examined as a court witness.","start":783.19,"stop":799.842,"duration":16.65},{"text":"Is that the fact?","start":799.842,"stop":800.824,"duration":0.98}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is the fact, Your Honor and it is so stated in the record and in fact Mr. Malmgren, the defense counsel said I will not state that she is unreliable.","start":800.824,"stop":811.465,"duration":10.64}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What was the statement based upon that she was unreliable.","start":811.465,"stop":816.843,"duration":5.38},{"text":"Is there anything to indicate that?","start":816.843,"stop":818.157,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh!","start":818.157,"stop":819.615,"duration":1.46},{"text":"No, no.","start":819.615,"stop":819.947,"duration":0.33},{"text":"The defense counsel would refuse to say that she was unreliable.","start":819.947,"stop":824.002,"duration":4.05},{"text":"His point was that he didn't know what her testimony was going to be and he couldn't risk being bound by her testimony.","start":824.002,"stop":831.36,"duration":7.36}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes, I understand that but I mean, has anything developed since to indicate that Mrs. Baxter was not reliable?","start":831.36,"stop":842.29,"duration":10.93}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":842.29,"stop":844.673,"duration":2.38},{"text":"I -- no.","start":844.673,"stop":845.876,"duration":1.2},{"text":"I would say, no.","start":845.876,"stop":847.239,"duration":1.36},{"text":"But there was some suggestion in the record that say that they put in an affidavit that she had given some contrary testimony -- made a contrary statement to a prosecution with -- that was introduced in '63.","start":847.239,"stop":862.58,"duration":15.34},{"text":"But when she -- but nobody has really challenged her for it.","start":862.58,"stop":866.985,"duration":4.4}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the importance?","start":866.985,"stop":868.883,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Because it --","start":868.883,"stop":869.581,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the importance that you attribute to the statement that a witness didn't have to talk to somebody on the outside if he didn't want to?","start":869.581,"stop":879.114,"duration":9.53}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice Black because it cut the defense off not only from this live witness.","start":879.114,"stop":884.924,"duration":5.81}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But he did cut the defense?","start":884.924,"stop":886.33,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":886.33,"stop":886.889,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you claim that a person who doesn't have a right to refuse to talk to somebody and tell him about the facts of the case before they put him on the stand?","start":886.889,"stop":896.856,"duration":9.97}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Our point is Your Honor that it was wrong for the prosecution to chill the defense in this avenue of exploration.","start":896.856,"stop":905.961,"duration":9.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"If they were asked a question, what is wrong with saying if you don't think you have to just talk to him unless you want to?","start":905.961,"stop":913.273,"duration":7.31}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Because in -- Your Honor, we feel that in a murder trial, particularly, that the defense is seriously handicapped if the prosecution compel --","start":913.273,"stop":924.33,"duration":11.06}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Admitting that --","start":924.33,"stop":925.569,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":925.569,"stop":925.577,"duration":0.01}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What I'm asking is, do you claim that because of anytime of trial, a person has got to talk to the lawyers or defendant in the case if he doesn't want to?","start":925.577,"stop":936.764,"duration":11.19}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No Your Honor, no.","start":936.764,"stop":938.039,"duration":1.27},{"text":"If this had been her --","start":938.039,"stop":938.623,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's why I can't understand the great emphasis because on that.","start":938.623,"stop":941.207,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No, only if she had said voluntarily of her own will, “I don't want to talk to you” then perfectly alright.","start":941.207,"stop":948.627,"duration":7.42},{"text":"But I think it was wrong for the prosecution to say to her to --","start":948.627,"stop":953.815,"duration":5.19}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you saying that the prosecution voluntarily went out of their way to tell a witness that they didn't have to talk -- I don't understand.","start":953.815,"stop":962.4,"duration":8.58},{"text":"That might have been thought of?","start":962.4,"stop":964.905,"duration":2.5}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"She called -- I believe that the record shows that she called the prosecuting attorney and then the prosecuting attorney --","start":964.905,"stop":971.737,"duration":6.83}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And asked him.","start":971.737,"stop":972.698,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"And asked him.","start":972.698,"stop":973.49,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"If she had to testify.","start":973.49,"stop":975.517,"duration":2.03}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Not to testify but to talk --","start":975.517,"stop":976.599,"duration":1.08}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That she had to talk to him.","start":976.599,"stop":977.851,"duration":1.25},{"text":"And he said --","start":977.851,"stop":977.988,"duration":0.14}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct.","start":977.988,"stop":978.549,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- she didn't have to.","start":978.549,"stop":980.024,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"She's -- he said --","start":980.024,"stop":980.627,"duration":0.6}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that the whole circumstance?","start":980.627,"stop":982.672,"duration":2.05}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He said that to her and to some certain other witnesses and the prosecutor so testified in '63.","start":982.672,"stop":989.507,"duration":6.83}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understand that but I think it's perfect and normal thing, it seems to me, if one person calls of another and asking the lawyer, “Do I have to talk on the outside?”","start":989.507,"stop":1001.931,"duration":12.42},{"text":"And said “No.”","start":1001.931,"stop":1003.676,"duration":1.75},{"text":"I don't quite understand the great emphasis you put on there.","start":1003.676,"stop":1006.736,"duration":3.06},{"text":"It may have it but I don't yet quite get it.","start":1006.736,"stop":1009.989,"duration":3.25}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the point is that if he had been allowed to complete that inquiry that then she would have been available as a witness.","start":1009.989,"stop":1020.614,"duration":10.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"If who had been allowed can be?","start":1020.614,"stop":1023.062,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"If the defense counsel had been allowed to --","start":1023.062,"stop":1025.414,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Then if the defense counsel --","start":1025.414,"stop":1026.806,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1026.806,"stop":1027.709,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- gotten this witness to talk, he could have found out more than he did.","start":1027.709,"stop":1031.366,"duration":3.66}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1031.366,"stop":1032.035,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But why do you attribute some wrongdoings of the prosecuting attorney and answer the question and saying you don't have to testify?","start":1032.035,"stop":1039.712,"duration":7.68}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we feel that his advice was wrong that she had a constitutional right and so forth.","start":1039.712,"stop":1045.501,"duration":5.79}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh!","start":1045.501,"stop":1045.753,"duration":0.25},{"text":"You think that she did not have a right to refrain from talking on the outside of the Court?","start":1045.753,"stop":1052.244,"duration":6.49}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"If it was up to her, she could make her own decision but the prosecution should --","start":1052.244,"stop":1055.868,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What you said so far, you've made it after her, but she called the prosecutor, you've said it?","start":1055.868,"stop":1060.349,"duration":4.48}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1060.349,"stop":1060.707,"duration":0.36}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And ask if she had to talk to this man and he said no.","start":1060.707,"stop":1066.187,"duration":5.48},{"text":"What's wrong with that?","start":1066.187,"stop":1068.262,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think you should have said to her in fairness to the defense that you go ahead -- he asked to prepare his case.","start":1068.262,"stop":1076.018,"duration":7.76},{"text":"I think that would've been the part where it is.","start":1076.018,"stop":1076.417,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't claim legal error for a prosecuting attorney to make that answer, do you?","start":1076.417,"stop":1081.876,"duration":5.46}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We do Your Honor.","start":1081.876,"stop":1084.396,"duration":2.52},{"text":"Well, we might mention also that the Gregory case which decided recently by the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia, somewhat similar circumstances.","start":1084.396,"stop":1094.629,"duration":10.23}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But would she have to testify?","start":1094.629,"stop":1096.942,"duration":2.31}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"She testified in 1963.","start":1096.942,"stop":1099.362,"duration":2.42}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But she didn't testify in the trial?","start":1099.362,"stop":1101.281,"duration":1.92}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No Mr. Justice White, she did not.","start":1101.281,"stop":1102.551,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"You contend that the state had information about what Mrs. Baxter might testify to and didn't reveal it to the prosecution?","start":1102.551,"stop":1112.525,"duration":9.97}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't know what they --","start":1112.525,"stop":1113.344,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you ever asked in the '63 hearing?","start":1113.344,"stop":1115.756,"duration":2.41},{"text":"Didn't you -- did you go into that matter whether these facts which Mrs. Baxter -- would you know Mrs. Baxter would testify to it?","start":1115.756,"stop":1127.272,"duration":11.52},{"text":"Did you ask the prosecution whether they lose out in '56?","start":1127.272,"stop":1130.742,"duration":3.47}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They put in their own evidence on that point.","start":1130.742,"stop":1134.033,"duration":3.29}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"On what point?","start":1134.033,"stop":1135.342,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They put in evidence saying that some official had interviewed her and she had told them -- given them a different story but she testified in '63, she and her husband and the two grandchildren, placing him in the house at the time of the crime.","start":1135.342,"stop":1155.303,"duration":19.96}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well so, she's given -- she essentially gave two different stories there.","start":1155.303,"stop":1160.32,"duration":5.02},{"text":"One in the prosecution and one in the --","start":1160.32,"stop":1161.903,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't say that Mr. Justice White because that was just a hearsay --","start":1161.903,"stop":1168.82,"duration":6.92}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, why --","start":1168.82,"stop":1169.545,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They just put it in an affidavit.","start":1169.545,"stop":1170.84,"duration":1.29},{"text":"They didn't put the man on the stand.","start":1170.84,"stop":1172.117,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, yes, the prosecution -- that's the prosecution's claim, isn't it?","start":1172.117,"stop":1175.961,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That's their claim, yes.","start":1175.961,"stop":1178.196,"duration":2.23}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And it's your claim that she has testified something else.","start":1178.196,"stop":1181.88,"duration":3.68}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1181.88,"stop":1182.514,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the affidavit of the prosecution as to what she said fit with the theory of their case as it was tried?","start":1182.514,"stop":1194.233,"duration":11.72}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it does.","start":1194.233,"stop":1200.059,"duration":5.83},{"text":"Thank you, Your Honor.","start":1200.059,"stop":1202.529,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Rosenfield.","start":1202.529,"stop":1212.695,"duration":10.17}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":1212.695,"stop":1216.872,"duration":4.18},{"text":"I appear here on behalf of two amici, the American Civil Liberties Union, Illinois Division and the Chicago Radio Station, WAIT.","start":1216.872,"stop":1230.414,"duration":13.54},{"text":"The amici are here because they believe of what is said to be a ghost which stalks the legal system.","start":1230.414,"stop":1240.481,"duration":10.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Ghost of what?","start":1240.481,"stop":1242.002,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"What is said to be a ghost, which stalks the legal system, the possibility of sentencing an innocent man to death has come to life in this case.","start":1242.002,"stop":1253.764,"duration":11.76},{"text":"We believe it has come to life in this case.","start":1253.764,"stop":1258.298,"duration":4.53},{"text":"We argue that police and prosecutor indecency measured by due process standards, concealed the innocence of this accused, petitioner here.","start":1258.298,"stop":1272.334,"duration":14.04},{"text":"The controlling case is Brady against Maryland.","start":1272.334,"stop":1275.898,"duration":3.56},{"text":"And the crucial point is the suppression of an official report of the State Bureau of Criminal Identification and Investigation to the effect that here, found in the vagina of a victim was not that of the accused.","start":1275.898,"stop":1297.038,"duration":21.14},{"text":"The crucial point is that this report was suppressed for eight years.","start":1297.038,"stop":1301.087,"duration":4.05},{"text":"It was known to the prosecution.","start":1301.087,"stop":1304.63,"duration":3.54},{"text":"It was sent to the prosecution.","start":1304.63,"stop":1306.634,"duration":2},{"text":"The prosecutors admitted the habeas corpus hearing that they knew about it.","start":1306.634,"stop":1311.191,"duration":4.56},{"text":"The report was never disclosed.","start":1311.191,"stop":1313.383,"duration":2.19},{"text":"It was brought to life for the first time in the habeas corpus proceeding in the federal court.","start":1313.383,"stop":1319.76,"duration":6.38}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any evidence adduced by the prosecution at the trial to the effect that this hair was from the body of the defendant?","start":1319.76,"stop":1333.388,"duration":13.63}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Hairs were not admitted at the trial at all.","start":1333.388,"stop":1335.822,"duration":2.43},{"text":"Nothing --","start":1335.822,"stop":1336.375,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"There is no evidence at all --","start":1336.375,"stop":1338.033,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No evidence at the trial at all on hairs.","start":1338.033,"stop":1340.501,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"And so this man --","start":1340.501,"stop":1341.627,"duration":1.13}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"All we know.","start":1341.627,"stop":1342.505,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"This man was convicted without any evidence at all --","start":1342.505,"stop":1345.379,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"About the hair.","start":1345.379,"stop":1345.854,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"- one way or the other --","start":1345.854,"stop":1346.723,"duration":0.87}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"One way or the other --","start":1346.723,"stop":1346.957,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that the hair is from his body?","start":1346.957,"stop":1348.674,"duration":1.72}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Crucial point.","start":1348.674,"stop":1349.194,"duration":0.52},{"text":"The point I'm making is that the official report of the state -- Criminal Investigation Department was exonerated, totally exonerated.","start":1349.194,"stop":1359.733,"duration":10.54},{"text":"It's impossible for the mind to conceive of any explanation for that hair of being in the vagina of the victim, other than it was a hair of the attacker.","start":1359.733,"stop":1370.988,"duration":11.26},{"text":"And this, we are told by recognized police manuals, all of the police manuals, happens frequently in rape and sex cases.","start":1370.988,"stop":1382.409,"duration":11.42},{"text":"In fact, the cardinal principle in the investigation of such cases according to the police manuals is to search for hairs.","start":1382.409,"stop":1392.261,"duration":9.85},{"text":"That was done.","start":1392.261,"stop":1394.783,"duration":2.52},{"text":"Now, the fact that it was in the vagina, stands admitted on this record by the Attorney General of Illinois.","start":1394.783,"stop":1403.959,"duration":9.18},{"text":"No question has been raised about that, no one has ever raised that question.","start":1403.959,"stop":1408.436,"duration":4.48},{"text":"And the critical point is the suppression of the report which is not an inference, that's null and that's admitted.","start":1408.436,"stop":1414.264,"duration":5.83},{"text":"The report was never disclosed.","start":1414.264,"stop":1417.218,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there any question as to whether this was a pubic hair or not?","start":1417.218,"stop":1421.383,"duration":4.16}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"We know for comparative purposes, Mr. Chief Justice that a pubic hair was taken from the accused.","start":1421.383,"stop":1429.25,"duration":7.87},{"text":"The nature of the hair in the child's vagina is not exactly known.","start":1429.25,"stop":1435.316,"duration":6.07},{"text":"Inference, I would think that it is pubic because the hair, the forensic medicine books tell us that hairs have different characteristics from the different parts of the body but I can't say that there's anything in the record.","start":1435.316,"stop":1449.134,"duration":13.82},{"text":"All we know that it was a hair, the probability is that it was a pubic hair in the vagina of an eight-year-old child.","start":1449.134,"stop":1457.64,"duration":8.51},{"text":"Now the --","start":1457.64,"stop":1458.087,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Your -- your position is a little different in that, isn't it?","start":1458.087,"stop":1461.92,"duration":3.83},{"text":"That is to say that there was a written report by --","start":1461.92,"stop":1466.765,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"There was a written report.","start":1466.765,"stop":1467.16,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- by a state scientist --","start":1467.16,"stop":1471.433,"duration":4.27}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Which came from the Department of Criminal Investigation.","start":1471.433,"stop":1475.22,"duration":3.79}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And that was in the possession of the prosecution at the time, before the trial and at the time of trial, is that right?","start":1475.22,"stop":1481.842,"duration":6.62}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes Mr. Justice Fortas, that's the point I was trying to make.","start":1481.842,"stop":1484.216,"duration":2.37}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And that said that there was a plastic container which contained two pubic hairs, one from the girl and the other that was found.","start":1484.216,"stop":1496.433,"duration":12.22}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No sir.","start":1496.433,"stop":1497.878,"duration":1.44},{"text":"It contained a vaginal smear, a vaginal -- a vaginal smear from the child.","start":1497.878,"stop":1503.831,"duration":5.95}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1503.831,"stop":1504.379,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"The vaginal smear was examined by the state department and the hair was discovered by the state department.","start":1504.379,"stop":1511.313,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1511.313,"stop":1511.781,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"When the accused was taken into custody, one of the -- virtually, the first act the police did was to take a pubic hair from him --","start":1511.781,"stop":1520.541,"duration":8.76}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I see.","start":1520.541,"stop":1520.942,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- for comparative purposes.","start":1520.942,"stop":1523.772,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And the -- and the report --","start":1523.772,"stop":1525.502,"duration":1.73}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"At that point, they recognized with the size of significance of the hair in the vial.","start":1525.502,"stop":1531.327,"duration":5.83}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And those two hairs were --","start":1531.327,"stop":1532.855,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Were compared --","start":1532.855,"stop":1533.756,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- by the state.","start":1533.756,"stop":1534.607,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and found to be a mismatch.","start":1534.607,"stop":1536.544,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And the state -- the state scientist who examined this so reported.","start":1536.544,"stop":1544.115,"duration":7.57}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"So reported.","start":1544.115,"stop":1545.082,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And that his written report so stated that it was in the possession of the prosecution before trial and at the time of trial, is that right?","start":1545.082,"stop":1554.152,"duration":9.07}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It was sent to the prosecution.","start":1554.152,"stop":1556.272,"duration":2.12},{"text":"It was in the hands of the prosecution, the facts that were known to the prosecution and that is what I meant to be saying is the report that was suppressed.","start":1556.272,"stop":1564.652,"duration":8.38}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, did the -- yes, I see.","start":1564.652,"stop":1570.256,"duration":5.6},{"text":"The hair that was in this plastic container or rather in the vaginal smear, was that identified as a pubic hair in the written report?","start":1570.256,"stop":1586.461,"duration":16.2}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That was -- the hair in the container was not identified in the report as a pubic hair.","start":1586.461,"stop":1594.069,"duration":7.61},{"text":"In answer to Mr. Chief Justice Warren a moment ago, I said that I thought the probability was high that it was a pubic hair because pubic hairs are known to have different characteristics from hairs of -- from other parts of the body.","start":1594.069,"stop":1610.156,"duration":16.09},{"text":"However, the report does not say that.","start":1610.156,"stop":1612.227,"duration":2.07},{"text":"It does state that the hair of the accused which was compared was a pubic hair and therefore it was found to be a mismatch.","start":1612.227,"stop":1620.791,"duration":8.56}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And your point, very simply stated is that whatever the inference may or may not be that this is relevant and of great importance as part of the trial and that the prosecution had a duty to advice a defense in its existence.","start":1620.791,"stop":1644.012,"duration":23.22}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That sir is exactly my point.","start":1644.012,"stop":1646.732,"duration":2.72}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was the confession that the -- that was introduced at the trial contested of being having been coerced?","start":1646.732,"stop":1659.098,"duration":12.37}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It was vigorously contested as having been coerced.","start":1659.098,"stop":1662.353,"duration":3.26}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the --","start":1662.353,"stop":1663.281,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It obviously does not meet Miranda standards but I'm not arguing that point.","start":1663.281,"stop":1666.903,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1666.903,"stop":1667.6,"duration":0.7},{"text":"Did the -- did the defendant testify on that proceeding?","start":1667.6,"stop":1672.491,"duration":4.89}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"The defendant did testify both in chambers, outside the presence of the jury and before the jury.The defendant denied -- at that point, he has denied consistently from that moment that he had ever confessed.","start":1672.491,"stop":1687.591,"duration":15.1},{"text":"He is claiming that the paper he signed, he didn't know what the paper was that it was a -- he was coaxed into signing this paper in order to avoid going to the electric chair after 52 hours of interrogation.","start":1687.591,"stop":1701.903,"duration":14.31}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does he mean --","start":1701.903,"stop":1702.149,"duration":0.25}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't mean to imply that all 52 hours involved interrogation after 52 hours of detention.","start":1702.149,"stop":1707.51,"duration":5.36}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he testify at that time that the police told him they had found the hair that matched with his?","start":1707.51,"stop":1718.809,"duration":11.3}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"He testified at that time and the episode is somewhat garbled.","start":1718.809,"stop":1723.877,"duration":5.07},{"text":"No one paid much attention to it because it was never known until eight years later in a habeas corpus proceeding that the state report existed, exonerating report existed.","start":1723.877,"stop":1732.983,"duration":9.11},{"text":"At that time, he testified that somewhere during the 52 hours of detention, he was somehow told that hair has incriminated him.","start":1732.983,"stop":1743.95,"duration":10.97},{"text":"That's all it appears that that hair is somehow incriminated him.","start":1743.95,"stop":1747.764,"duration":3.81},{"text":"It does not appear that it was told that a hair was in the child's vagina.","start":1747.764,"stop":1751.807,"duration":4.04},{"text":"He was simply told that the hair has incriminated him.","start":1751.807,"stop":1754.48,"duration":2.67},{"text":"He asked, he jumped to the microscope himself and said let me look and “them hairs don't match”.","start":1754.48,"stop":1765.777,"duration":11.3},{"text":"This is his testimony at the trial in the trial record and it's all we know about the hair episode.","start":1765.777,"stop":1772.555,"duration":6.78}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, when that was raised by the defendant, did the prosecution respond to it in anyway?","start":1772.555,"stop":1778.865,"duration":6.31}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It did not respond to it.","start":1778.865,"stop":1781.563,"duration":2.7},{"text":"It did not respond to it any way.","start":1781.563,"stop":1783.133,"duration":1.57},{"text":"It was not counted.","start":1783.133,"stop":1786.198,"duration":3.07},{"text":"When -- I might say this Mr. Chief Justice, when the accused counsel were permitted to look at the state's evidence, there were hair, hairs were among the evidence exhibited to them but no -- not the report just for hairs as evidence that the state would rely upon, so as counsel would be jumped or they form the opinion if the hairs were somehow favorable to the state.","start":1786.198,"stop":1814.227,"duration":28.03},{"text":"Hairs were among the evidence exhibited --","start":1814.227,"stop":1820.142,"duration":5.91}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"When was it exhibited?","start":1820.142,"stop":1820.732,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Some point before the -- at some point before the trial.","start":1820.732,"stop":1824.228,"duration":3.5},{"text":"Not the report.","start":1824.228,"stop":1825.316,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but at that point, could the -- could the matter of the examination had been pursued which had been previously turned down.","start":1825.316,"stop":1833.827,"duration":8.51},{"text":"You told to Mr. Justice Fortas that there had been a motion and a denial in May.","start":1833.827,"stop":1839.222,"duration":5.39},{"text":"And when it was the -- when the physical evidence was finally exhibited to the defense, at that point, did the defense had an opportunity to pursue the matter of an examination?","start":1839.222,"stop":1851.623,"duration":12.4}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"They did not have an opportunity.","start":1851.623,"stop":1853.519,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they attempt to?","start":1853.519,"stop":1854.584,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"They asked.","start":1854.584,"stop":1855.937,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"At that time also?","start":1855.937,"stop":1857.588,"duration":1.65}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"At that -- I don't -- all that appears in the record is that they ask several times.","start":1857.588,"stop":1861.788,"duration":4.2},{"text":"How many times?","start":1861.788,"stop":1862.41,"duration":0.62},{"text":"We don't know.","start":1862.41,"stop":1863.48,"duration":1.07},{"text":"The prosecutor testified for habeas corpus proceeding that they asked continuously.","start":1863.48,"stop":1867.757,"duration":4.28}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Asked what?","start":1867.757,"stop":1868.731,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Asked for permission to examine the physical evidence, the point that Mr. Lassers --","start":1868.731,"stop":1872.669,"duration":3.94}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought you said they had it and was presented?","start":1872.669,"stop":1875.024,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"They were permitted to look at it.","start":1875.024,"stop":1876.914,"duration":1.89},{"text":"Look -- simply to look at it.","start":1876.914,"stop":1878.998,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But couldn't they protect it?","start":1878.998,"stop":1880.791,"duration":1.79}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That I don't know.","start":1880.791,"stop":1882.296,"duration":1.51},{"text":"They were just permitted to look at it.","start":1882.296,"stop":1883.387,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It was turned over to them to look at.","start":1883.387,"stop":1885.468,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Or --","start":1885.468,"stop":1886.332,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Or was it?","start":1886.332,"stop":1887.096,"duration":0.76}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know.","start":1887.096,"stop":1887.67,"duration":0.57},{"text":"The record is silent at it.","start":1887.67,"stop":1889.326,"duration":1.66},{"text":"So I simply don't know.","start":1889.326,"stop":1889.77,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So we don't know whether it was turned over to them to look at it?","start":1889.77,"stop":1892.103,"duration":2.33}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Or it was just -- or it was just open to their examination and -- at some place or some point.","start":1892.103,"stop":1901.116,"duration":9.01},{"text":"Mr. Lassers tells me, in the presence of the sheriff, they were permitted to see --","start":1901.116,"stop":1907.649,"duration":6.53}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But it was not -- none of these things was surrendered to them?","start":1907.649,"stop":1911.093,"duration":3.44}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"None of these things were surrendered to them.","start":1911.093,"stop":1913.302,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, may I ask --","start":1913.302,"stop":1913.702,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't suppose it should have been surrendered to them really.","start":1913.702,"stop":1919.648,"duration":5.95}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- if this --","start":1919.648,"stop":1920.022,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose the state would want to keep it if it was evidence.","start":1920.022,"stop":1922.854,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon, Mr. Justice Black.","start":1922.854,"stop":1923.723,"duration":0.87}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose the state would want to keep it if it was evidence.","start":1923.723,"stop":1927.349,"duration":3.63}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, so the District Court but all things there were made available for scientific -- for examination by the --","start":1927.349,"stop":1932.092,"duration":4.74}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I thought (Voice Overlap).","start":1932.092,"stop":1933.36,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"By the Federal District Court.","start":1933.36,"stop":1936.063,"duration":2.7}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But what -- I'm not sure yet about this testimony in the accused himself about the hairs and he's looking into the microscope and so forth that this -- was that testimony the testimony that he gave at the trial in connection with the challenge to the admissibility of the confession?","start":1936.063,"stop":1954.295,"duration":18.23}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It was sir.","start":1954.295,"stop":1955.217,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And was that out of the presence of the jury?","start":1955.217,"stop":1956.937,"duration":1.72}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It was out of the presence of the jury.","start":1956.937,"stop":1959.236,"duration":2.3},{"text":"It was at the hearing on the admissibility of the confession in which he was recounting chronologically what happened to him during the 52-hour incommunicado detention period.","start":1959.236,"stop":1972.781,"duration":13.54},{"text":"Now, the treatment of this point --","start":1972.781,"stop":1973.956,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the record show whether the hairs themselves were in the Courtroom on the occasion of that testimony?","start":1973.956,"stop":1980.088,"duration":6.13}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It does not show.","start":1980.088,"stop":1981.5,"duration":1.41},{"text":"The report certainly was not, the exonerating report.","start":1981.5,"stop":1985.667,"duration":4.17}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And that I gather when -- after the confession was admitted, the state as part of its case, I think you've already told us, offered no hairs as exhibit.","start":1985.667,"stop":1996.718,"duration":11.05}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"They offered no hairs as part of their case.","start":1996.718,"stop":2001.07,"duration":4.35},{"text":"Now, the Attorney General in response to all of these about the hair offers two points.","start":2001.07,"stop":2006.982,"duration":5.91},{"text":"One point is a formal one that no request was made by the accused counsel of -- for the evidence we claim was suppressed.","start":2006.982,"stop":2020.075,"duration":13.09},{"text":"This, we are submitting to Your Honors, that the Brady against Maryland cannot be read as requiring such a request and we have cited the case, U.S. versus Wilkins decided by Judge Thurgood Marshall which reviews all the authorities on this.","start":2020.075,"stop":2038.842,"duration":18.77},{"text":"Incidentally, this point was very similar to the point that bothered the Court before the Jencks case.","start":2038.842,"stop":2046.587,"duration":7.74},{"text":"It was very much the same point that a report was available to contradict and the question was raised and the point was made in Mr. Justice Brennan's opinion in the Jencks case that how could anyone be expected to know the contents of report they hadn't seen.","start":2046.587,"stop":2064.904,"duration":18.32},{"text":"The other point that the Attorney General makes is that the accused himself somehow knew because of this colloquy that took place during the 52-hour detention period.","start":2064.904,"stop":2081.147,"duration":16.24},{"text":"Note, the Attorney General is in the awkward position of claiming that the accused -- a statement they made to the accused that hairs matched is to be treated as fulfillment of their obligation under the Constitution to disclose that the hairs did not match.","start":2081.147,"stop":2100.258,"duration":19.11},{"text":"Now, there was no disclosure at all that the hair within the child's vagina didn't match the accused hair.","start":2100.258,"stop":2109.257,"duration":9},{"text":"There was simply some general garble conversation during this long detention period about hairs.","start":2109.257,"stop":2117.672,"duration":8.41}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"How old is he now?","start":2117.672,"stop":2119.748,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"He's been in the death house ten years.","start":2119.748,"stop":2121.953,"duration":2.2},{"text":"He's approximately 30 years of age at the time of his conviction.","start":2121.953,"stop":2126.129,"duration":4.18},{"text":"He's 40 years here of age.","start":2126.129,"stop":2130.181,"duration":4.05}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What you're saying is that whatever the hairs were that he saw during was 52 hours, were never identified by the prosecution as one of them being a hair from the child.","start":2130.181,"stop":2140.771,"duration":10.59}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Never so identified, Mr. Justice Brennan, that's just what I'm saying yes sir.","start":2140.771,"stop":2146.478,"duration":5.71},{"text":"Now, an electrocution for this man was averted six hours before it was to occur only as a result of the intervention of the United States District Court in the habeas corpus case.","start":2146.478,"stop":2167.467,"duration":20.99},{"text":"The District Court reached the correct result perhaps for wrong reasons.","start":2167.467,"stop":2173.154,"duration":5.69},{"text":"The Court of Appeals reached the wrong result for clearly wrong reasons.","start":2173.154,"stop":2178.224,"duration":5.07},{"text":"And we ask this Court to reach the right result for the right reason.","start":2178.224,"stop":2183.554,"duration":5.33},{"text":"I thank you.","start":2183.554,"stop":2186.436,"duration":2.88}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael.","start":2186.436,"stop":2192.883,"duration":6.45}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":2192.883,"stop":2197.165,"duration":4.28},{"text":"The contentions of the petitioner in this case can be basically summarized into two broad categories, one, the lack of access to certain information, and secondly, the validity of the admission of his confession at the trial.","start":2197.165,"stop":2216.55,"duration":19.39},{"text":"Concerning first, the issue of the defense's access to information perhaps their most significant issue is that of the finding of the hair.","start":2216.55,"stop":2230.196,"duration":13.65},{"text":"Now, with respect to this issue, it is important to first determine what was revealed and what was not revealed.","start":2230.196,"stop":2241.003,"duration":10.81},{"text":"At the District Court, when the petitioner testified, he testified that when in those same proceedings he had heard the state's attorney testify as to the result of this examination.","start":2241.003,"stop":2252.082,"duration":11.08},{"text":"This was the first he had ever heard about that hair.","start":2252.082,"stop":2255.937,"duration":3.86},{"text":"However, this conclusion is cast into doubt by his testimony at the trial itself.","start":2255.937,"stop":2263.44,"duration":7.5},{"text":"Now, I'm talking about the chambers testimony that he gave when the question of his -- the admissibility of his confession first arose for the determination by the Court before it was submitted to the jury.","start":2263.44,"stop":2279.471,"duration":16.03},{"text":"At that time, he testified that in effect he testified, “They took some pubic hairs from me.","start":2279.471,"stop":2292.431,"duration":12.96},{"text":"They told me that another hair that it matched with.","start":2292.431,"stop":2295.171,"duration":2.74},{"text":"I demand to look in the comparative microscope.","start":2295.171,"stop":2298.59,"duration":3.42},{"text":"I looked, and I said those hairs don't match.","start":2298.59,"stop":2301.546,"duration":2.96},{"text":"I'm just using the exact language with --","start":2301.546,"stop":2302.664,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Who said that now?","start":2302.664,"stop":2303.836,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"This was the petitioner, Your Honor.","start":2303.836,"stop":2305.825,"duration":1.99}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"The defendant?","start":2305.825,"stop":2306.458,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The defendant at the trial, yes Your Honor.","start":2306.458,"stop":2308.034,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Did that happen in the stated -- did that happen during the 52 hour detention?","start":2308.034,"stop":2312.699,"duration":4.66}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It -- he testified to it, Your Honor.","start":2312.699,"stop":2315.802,"duration":3.1},{"text":"As far as I know it is un-contradicted testimony in the record.","start":2315.802,"stop":2318.487,"duration":2.68}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"So we can take that as true, that's what happened?","start":2318.487,"stop":2321.798,"duration":3.31}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I think that that is a fair statement on the basis of this record Your Honor.","start":2321.798,"stop":2324.891,"duration":3.09}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And did he also say that, might be, they said that, in the record, state officials told him during that period that they had hairs which proved his guilt as to that effect?","start":2324.891,"stop":2337.474,"duration":12.58}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll give you the exact language, Your Honor.","start":2337.474,"stop":2350.298,"duration":12.82},{"text":"Try Volume 4, the Court will refer to this as the brown record, Volume 4, page 91 in 273 and 95.","start":2350.298,"stop":2364.818,"duration":14.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What page again did you say Mr. --?","start":2364.818,"stop":2368.769,"duration":3.95},{"text":"What page did you say again?","start":2368.769,"stop":2372.363,"duration":3.59}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"First we'll start, Your Honor with page 90.","start":2372.363,"stop":2374.936,"duration":2.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"90, thank you.","start":2374.936,"stop":2377.927,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"At that point, he testified, about the middle of the second paragraph on page -- first full paragraph on page 90.","start":2377.927,"stop":2385.309,"duration":7.38},{"text":"Also, they took a small quantity of hair from around my privates.","start":2385.309,"stop":2388.551,"duration":3.24}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"This was testimony outside of the presence of the jury.","start":2388.551,"stop":2392.218,"duration":3.67}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes it was, Your Honor.","start":2392.218,"stop":2393.056,"duration":0.84},{"text":"This was on the admissibility of the confession.","start":2393.056,"stop":2399.074,"duration":6.02},{"text":"At page 95 then Your Honors, I refer you next to that, the first full paragraph on page 95.","start":2399.074,"stop":2408.043,"duration":8.97},{"text":"He says, “I was in this little room at all times in the evening of November 30, except for one time when I demanded to look through the microscope my own self, because they said these hairs belong to me.","start":2408.043,"stop":2418.303,"duration":10.26},{"text":"Mr. Lich made a statement to me that certain hairs belonged to me.","start":2418.303,"stop":2421.112,"duration":2.81},{"text":"He showed me some hairs there.","start":2421.112,"stop":2423.24,"duration":2.13},{"text":"I demanded to go back and he took me there back into the laboratory and a small room which appeared to be a microscope room.","start":2423.24,"stop":2428.535,"duration":5.3},{"text":"And I looked down and I said them hairs don't match.","start":2428.535,"stop":2431.188,"duration":2.65},{"text":"I said them hairs don't belong to me.","start":2431.188,"stop":2433.052,"duration":1.86},{"text":"And the chemist just looked at me and smiled.”","start":2433.052,"stop":2435.924,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, that was a couple of days after his arrest, was it not?","start":2435.924,"stop":2440.549,"duration":4.63}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not positive whether this -- yes on November 30, he was arrested on the 28, I believe, this was the 30th.","start":2440.549,"stop":2446.89,"duration":6.34}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And he's arrested on the 28th and on the 30th according to his testimony anyway, he was confronted with these hairs.","start":2446.89,"stop":2454.041,"duration":7.15}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2454.041,"stop":2454.371,"duration":0.33}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"What's the date of the confession?","start":2454.371,"stop":2456.335,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The confession is the 30th, Your Honor, the same day in which he was confronted with these hairs.","start":2456.335,"stop":2467.317,"duration":10.98}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, did you say another page?","start":2467.317,"stop":2468.837,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought I did, Your Honor, I was looking for it and I don't --","start":2468.837,"stop":2470.961,"duration":2.12}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"The 273?","start":2470.961,"stop":2472.365,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"273, well that's just a repetition of the first statement, Your Honor.","start":2472.365,"stop":2484.565,"duration":12.2},{"text":"This is at his testimony, this narrows his testimony, I believe, before the jury.","start":2484.565,"stop":2495.334,"duration":10.77}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"For the jury?","start":2495.334,"stop":2496.397,"duration":1.06}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"This is his testimony before the jury at 273.","start":2496.397,"stop":2499.845,"duration":3.45},{"text":"All he testified here Your Honor is he said, “Then they took a bunch of hairs from around my privates.”","start":2499.845,"stop":2504.546,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he tell the jury that?","start":2504.546,"stop":2506.328,"duration":1.78}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Apparently so, Your Honor.","start":2506.328,"stop":2507.484,"duration":1.16},{"text":"I'm trying to -- yes, this was before the jury.","start":2507.484,"stop":2516.445,"duration":8.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So he testified before the jury about the hair, did he not?","start":2516.445,"stop":2519.721,"duration":3.28}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He testified only, Your Honor, that they took some hair from him.","start":2519.721,"stop":2523.112,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Not that they showed him any as noted.","start":2523.112,"stop":2524.734,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no Your Honor, not as he did before the -- and before the Court in private when he testified that they had showed him this hair.","start":2524.734,"stop":2535.259,"duration":10.53}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he testify before the jury on -- just on the confession in which your Illinois procedure.","start":2535.259,"stop":2541.845,"duration":6.59},{"text":"Was that sworn testimony?","start":2541.845,"stop":2545.574,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Before the jury, no Your Honor, or before in the --","start":2545.574,"stop":2547.861,"duration":2.29}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Before the jury.","start":2547.861,"stop":2548.829,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Before the jury, it was sworn testimony.","start":2548.829,"stop":2550.257,"duration":1.43},{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":2550.257,"stop":2550.353,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Sworn testimony.","start":2550.353,"stop":2550.436,"duration":0.08}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Sure.","start":2550.436,"stop":2555.335,"duration":4.9}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was he cross-examined on that testimony?","start":2555.335,"stop":2558.251,"duration":2.92}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He was cross-examined, but I don't believe about that -- the point that we're talking about, Your Honor.","start":2558.251,"stop":2563.212,"duration":4.96}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, was counsel correct when he said that the state made no mention about the -- of the hairs in the whole file?","start":2563.212,"stop":2571.914,"duration":8.7}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"That is my understanding of the record, yes Your Honor.","start":2571.914,"stop":2575.966,"duration":4.05},{"text":"Now --","start":2575.966,"stop":2577.13,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, was that because the state decided it was not his hair?","start":2577.13,"stop":2581.935,"duration":4.8},{"text":"Do you know why?","start":2581.935,"stop":2584.251,"duration":2.32}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"All I can do is make an inference from the record, Your Honor.","start":2584.251,"stop":2587.255,"duration":3},{"text":"My inference from the record is that they did have this report showing that it was not his hair, and therefore never raised that issue at trial.","start":2587.255,"stop":2596.21,"duration":8.95}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But they did raise it at trial.","start":2596.21,"stop":2599.536,"duration":3.33},{"text":"You concede now that he has -- that we have to take it if they did tell him these hairs were his when at the time they were interrogating him before he signed his confession.","start":2599.536,"stop":2614.097,"duration":14.56},{"text":"Although they knew then that at least the one that was found on the child's vagina was not his, that --","start":2614.097,"stop":2618.749,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no I beg to differ with you on that Your Honor.","start":2618.749,"stop":2622.536,"duration":3.79}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what is the fact?","start":2622.536,"stop":2624.081,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The fact is that this interrogation as we said came back the 30th.","start":2624.081,"stop":2628.162,"duration":4.08}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2628.162,"stop":2628.338,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It was taken place in November 30th.","start":2628.338,"stop":2630.277,"duration":1.94},{"text":"They did not get the report, the scientific report as to the result of the comparison of these hairs until December 15, I believe it was.","start":2630.277,"stop":2639.347,"duration":9.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why did they tell him that they did match?","start":2639.347,"stop":2643.327,"duration":3.98}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I do not know, Your Honor.","start":2643.327,"stop":2644.185,"duration":0.86},{"text":"Perhaps the person who looked in the comparison microscope thought they did, but the record is -- has no information to guide us along those lines Your Honor.","start":2644.185,"stop":2654.43,"duration":10.24}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"What's the states view on the significance on the fact that on December 15, the state learned that these hairs did not match.","start":2654.43,"stop":2669.02,"duration":14.59},{"text":"And that the state apparently concedes that the hair found on the smear came from the girl.","start":2669.02,"stop":2680.083,"duration":11.06}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think that that is an inference that the prosecution made at the -- made and I think that I would've done this if I were to try to contradict that it as --","start":2680.083,"stop":2689.87,"duration":9.79}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"That means your brief, as I read your brief, you concede the hair came from the vagina of the girl.","start":2689.87,"stop":2695.979,"duration":6.11}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly, it was found on a Kleenex that it had been used to take a vaginal smear.","start":2695.979,"stop":2701.809,"duration":5.83},{"text":"I think that it is perfectly fair to make the assumption that that came from the vagina of the girl.","start":2701.809,"stop":2706.943,"duration":5.13}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And do you agree that it was a pubic hair?","start":2706.943,"stop":2710.761,"duration":3.82}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No I do not Your Honor.","start":2710.761,"stop":2712.007,"duration":1.25},{"text":"The report of the chemist merely identified that was hair of human origin.","start":2712.007,"stop":2716.492,"duration":4.49},{"text":"That is as far as we know.","start":2716.492,"stop":2719.299,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But it's -- let's assume the defense had information that a hair was found in the vagina of the little girl and that it didn't match the pubic hair of the defendant.","start":2719.299,"stop":2737.046,"duration":17.75},{"text":"I would suppose the defense would've put that testimony on before the jury, wouldn't it?","start":2737.046,"stop":2747.303,"duration":10.26}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not quite sure that I followed your question, Mr. Justice White.","start":2747.303,"stop":2750.289,"duration":2.99},{"text":"Would you repeat it again, please?","start":2750.289,"stop":2752.2,"duration":1.91}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I just wonder if the information the state had on December 15th from that report was of great interest for the defense.","start":2752.2,"stop":2761.249,"duration":9.05}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"That they should have revealed it.","start":2761.249,"stop":2763.583,"duration":2.33}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2763.583,"stop":2764.548,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, of course we --","start":2764.548,"stop":2765.416,"duration":0.87}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I don't -- unless we break that in two parts, let's forget about should've revealed from then.","start":2765.416,"stop":2771.416,"duration":6},{"text":"If you were defending and had that kind of information, would you introduce it to the trial?","start":2771.416,"stop":2779.993,"duration":8.58}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think as the prosecution, Your Honor, that certainly if I had this sort of information that I would not introduce into my case in chief, no.","start":2779.993,"stop":2788.998,"duration":9.01}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but if you were defending.","start":2788.998,"stop":2790.456,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, if were defending, yes I would, Your Honor.","start":2790.456,"stop":2792.213,"duration":1.76}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But do you suppose it would've affected the outcome of that trial?","start":2792.213,"stop":2795.394,"duration":3.18},{"text":"If the defense has had evidence that there has been found in the child a hair and that it was not the hair of the accused, if that evidence has been before the jury, do you suppose it might have affected the outcome of the term?","start":2795.394,"stop":2812.756,"duration":17.36}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"We are of course, Your Honor, dealing in a realm of supposition here.","start":2812.756,"stop":2814.923,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I know, but that --","start":2814.923,"stop":2815.919,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would --","start":2815.919,"stop":2815.964,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the test and on a few is whether it would affect the outcome of the trial, isn't it?","start":2815.964,"stop":2820.594,"duration":4.63}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would submit --","start":2820.594,"stop":2821.317,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It might affect the outcome of the trial.","start":2821.317,"stop":2823.187,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would submit, Your Honor, that when we had before the jury, his own confession, a admission that he made to Betty Baldwin, and we have the profession of prior admission of guilt, the fact of a hair in the vagina which did not match his, I submit to you, would not have changed the result before that jury.","start":2823.187,"stop":2842.96,"duration":19.77}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what's the -- how typical do that in this case -- differently in the case?","start":2842.96,"stop":2848.895,"duration":5.93}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael, as I understand it, you do not now represent to this Court that the hair which was found in the vaginal smear was not pubic hair.","start":2848.895,"stop":2866.273,"duration":17.38},{"text":"You don't make that representation --","start":2866.273,"stop":2868.279,"duration":2.01}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I make the --","start":2868.279,"stop":2868.436,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to concede the contrary.","start":2868.436,"stop":2871.258,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I make the representation Your Honor that the record shows that it was a hair of human origin.","start":2871.258,"stop":2875.008,"duration":3.75},{"text":"That it does not show that it was pubic hair.","start":2875.008,"stop":2876.657,"duration":1.65},{"text":"It does not show that it was not a pubic hair.","start":2876.657,"stop":2878.639,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And you do not here contend that it was not pubic hair?","start":2878.639,"stop":2886.165,"duration":7.53}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I do contend that it was not shown to be a pubic hair, Your Honor.","start":2886.165,"stop":2889.392,"duration":3.23}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand you.","start":2889.392,"stop":2892.189,"duration":2.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I wonder if this is impertinent.","start":2892.189,"stop":2895.712,"duration":3.52},{"text":"When on the motion to suppress the confession made out of the presence of the jury, when the defendant told the Court that while he was in jail they had shown him -- they had told him first that his pubic hairs matched with those found in the girl, and that he been looked at the microscope and -- himself and then said, “Those are not -- those don't match.","start":2895.712,"stop":2929.101,"duration":33.39},{"text":"They're not my hairs.”","start":2929.101,"stop":2932.107,"duration":3.01},{"text":"And the state had this report from its own laboratory to the effect that they did not match.","start":2932.107,"stop":2943.319,"duration":11.21},{"text":"Do you not think there was an obligation on the state to disclose the fact that it did have such a report and that it was consistent with what the defendant said?","start":2943.319,"stop":2956.863,"duration":13.54}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I submit that on the basis of this record, the duty to disclose is not present for three reasons.","start":2956.863,"stop":2964.799,"duration":7.94},{"text":"First, I submit that in effect, we can look at it that there was really no nondisclosure at all.","start":2964.799,"stop":2972.215,"duration":7.42},{"text":"He was told, according to the petitioner's testimony that a hair was found in the vagina of the victim that it matched his -- I beg your pardon that his were taken for comparison purposes and a comparison was going to be made.","start":2972.215,"stop":2985.585,"duration":13.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I understand that he testified that they said that they did match his and that there's no denial on that on the part of the state.","start":2985.585,"stop":2994.07,"duration":8.49}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"There was a denial by the petitioner, Your Honor.","start":2994.07,"stop":2997.601,"duration":3.53},{"text":"He was allowed to look into the microscope and said those hairs don't match.","start":2997.601,"stop":3001.752,"duration":4.15}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but the state had already told him that they did match and he says that they didn't.","start":3001.752,"stop":3009.296,"duration":7.54}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it say they didn't?","start":3009.296,"stop":3009.953,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And by the time the hearing came on, on the motion to suppress the state had a record from its laboratory to the effect that they did not match.","start":3009.953,"stop":3021.082,"duration":11.13},{"text":"Now, do you not think that those are burden on the -- on the state to admit to the Court that that was a fact rather than leave it to the Court to believe that what they had told him about the matching was true and that what he said about the not matching was not true?","start":3021.082,"stop":3041.648,"duration":20.57}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe there is some burden here Your Honor upon the prosecution -- upon the defense.","start":3041.648,"stop":3047.402,"duration":5.75},{"text":"This statement was made in the -- the statement was made, the question could've been asked by the defense.","start":3047.402,"stop":3055.318,"duration":7.92},{"text":"The defense could've made a motion for -- the defense knew Your Honor that there was a hair found in the vagina of the victim.","start":3055.318,"stop":3062.685,"duration":7.37},{"text":"They knew that his were being taken for comparison purposes.","start":3062.685,"stop":3067.905,"duration":5.22},{"text":"They never -- they had enough information Your Honor in closing argument and nothing else had been done to make -- to argue in closing argument to say, “Ladies and gentlemen of the jury, the state knew that there was hair found in the vagina of the victim.”","start":3067.905,"stop":3081.484,"duration":13.58},{"text":"The state took, mere comparison with the defendant's and they never introduced that at trial, except the information was totally in the hands of the defense, the inference can be drawn that that -- I beg your pardon Your Honor, the prosecution.","start":3081.484,"stop":3096.147,"duration":14.66},{"text":"The inference can be drawn that that hair was -- that that evidence was unfavorable.","start":3096.147,"stop":3100.787,"duration":4.64},{"text":"They had that amount of information in their possession, Your Honor.","start":3100.787,"stop":3104.326,"duration":3.54}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael, may I ask you questions?","start":3104.326,"stop":3107.12,"duration":2.79},{"text":"Suppose that the report, I'm trying to get the state's position now, suppose at the written report in the hands of the state were to the effect that the -- in the smear, there was found a hair, that is a pubic hair, you think that it was found in the little girl, and that the pubic hair that was found there did not match the pubic hair of the defendant.","start":3107.12,"stop":3144.463,"duration":37.34},{"text":"Let's suppose in other words that these were -- this sort of overwhelmingly exonerating report.","start":3144.463,"stop":3152.081,"duration":7.62},{"text":"In your -- in the state's position, would the state be obligated to disclose that to the defense?","start":3152.081,"stop":3160.899,"duration":8.82},{"text":"I think perhaps from my point of view that may be close to the knob of our problem.","start":3160.899,"stop":3167.561,"duration":6.66}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, we of course start with the -- with your proposition with Brady versus Maryland holds that evidence favorable to an accused relevant material to the evidence of either guilt or punishment in the hands of the -- on request, must be revealed.","start":3167.561,"stop":3187.685,"duration":20.12},{"text":"We start with that as our basic proposition.","start":3187.685,"stop":3190.734,"duration":3.05},{"text":"So then we ask on applying that proposition to the facts of the -- if I may, to the facts of this case first.","start":3190.734,"stop":3199.712,"duration":8.98},{"text":"We submit that first there was really no nondisclosure.","start":3199.712,"stop":3204.186,"duration":4.47},{"text":"We submit that he knew the hair was found in the vagina of the victim.","start":3204.186,"stop":3207.372,"duration":3.19},{"text":"We knew that his were being taken for comparison purposes.","start":3207.372,"stop":3210.257,"duration":2.89},{"text":"We know that he stated on the record that those hairs did not match him that that was never denied.","start":3210.257,"stop":3216.661,"duration":6.4},{"text":"As thus interpreted, he knew the hair was found.","start":3216.661,"stop":3220.424,"duration":3.76},{"text":"He knew what comparison was made.","start":3220.424,"stop":3223.035,"duration":2.61},{"text":"He knew that they didn't matched, if we can put any credence in his own ability to compare, and I don't know enough about the hair examination to know that if a layman looks in that he can see whether it's obvious that hairs match or do not match.","start":3223.035,"stop":3237.517,"duration":14.48},{"text":"But nevertheless, he admittedly denied it, immediately upon looking on it, immediately denied it and that denial was never denied.","start":3237.517,"stop":3245.289,"duration":7.77}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I know but maybe there are some limits to looking upon a capital case which the state demands a man's life and there are some limits to looking upon it as solely upon test of wits and abilities.","start":3245.289,"stop":3261.791,"duration":16.5},{"text":"And that's why I'm asking you what state's position is on the assumption that I stated.That is say let's suppose if this were --","start":3261.791,"stop":3271.01,"duration":9.22}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If a proper --","start":3271.01,"stop":3271.218,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- regular court where totally exonerating and let's suppose that the defense, because of negligence or stupidity or whatever, did not demand the production of the report or because they didn't know of its existence, which I take it, is a fact here, did not demand the production of it.","start":3271.218,"stop":3294.007,"duration":22.79},{"text":"Do you think that the state would be justified as a constitutional matter in not volunteering that information?","start":3294.007,"stop":3306.464,"duration":12.46}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would assume, Your Honor that if one, you can see the materiality of this testimony.","start":3306.464,"stop":3312.771,"duration":6.31},{"text":"Now, I must add in answering this question that both the District Court and the Court of Appeals based their decision on this point upon, the question of materiality of the evidence.","start":3312.771,"stop":3326.541,"duration":13.77},{"text":"The District Court stated the hair found in the vagina of the victim was of not consequence and did not prejudice the petitioner's case.","start":3326.541,"stop":3335.612,"duration":9.07},{"text":"The Court of Appeals stated, there is absolutely no evidence in the record to show that that hair was in the vagina was of the perpetrator of the crime, and they further held that on the basis of the damaged condition of the body, it could've been deposited by anybody who had examined the body or anybody who had handled the body since the crime.","start":3335.612,"stop":3360.74,"duration":25.13},{"text":"That was the conclusion of the Court of Appeals, Your Honor.","start":3360.74,"stop":3364.251,"duration":3.51},{"text":"So, but if we assume the materiality of the evidence, if we assume a proper request was made as envisioned by Brady versus Maryland, I then ask you that that information would have to be divulged, yes sir.","start":3364.251,"stop":3377.554,"duration":13.3}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"That of course is not my question, but that's alright, go ahead now.","start":3377.554,"stop":3383.997,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have that pubic hair now or that hair?","start":3383.997,"stop":3388.269,"duration":4.27}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I do not believe that it is amongst the exhibits now.","start":3388.269,"stop":3391.154,"duration":2.89},{"text":"Maybe you know that it is not presently amongst the exhibit.","start":3391.154,"stop":3394.109,"duration":2.95}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It's not in existence?","start":3394.109,"stop":3396.38,"duration":2.27}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If it is in existence, I do not know where it is, Your Honor.","start":3396.38,"stop":3400.229,"duration":3.85}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the doctor who made the report record whether it was a pubic hair or not a pubic hair?","start":3400.229,"stop":3404.071,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No he did not, Your Honor.","start":3404.071,"stop":3405.701,"duration":1.63},{"text":"I don't -- I beg your pardon, there was no doctor's report on that, Your Honor.","start":3405.701,"stop":3409.075,"duration":3.37},{"text":"There was a chemist report.","start":3409.075,"stop":3410.748,"duration":1.67},{"text":"The chemist did not -- only reported that it was hair of human origin, probably of human origin.","start":3410.748,"stop":3416.322,"duration":5.57},{"text":"He uses this --","start":3416.322,"stop":3416.362,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did not report whether it was pubic hair.","start":3416.362,"stop":3418.852,"duration":2.49}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"They did not, Your Honor.","start":3418.852,"stop":3420.956,"duration":2.1}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any testimony about whether there could've been any hair there from her own body at her age?","start":3420.956,"stop":3428.667,"duration":7.71}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not sure whether there was or not, Your Honor.","start":3428.667,"stop":3432.07,"duration":3.4},{"text":"I believe there was not, but I just am not sure of that.","start":3432.07,"stop":3438.308,"duration":6.24}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But you have no way of knowing now whether it was a pubic hair or not?","start":3438.308,"stop":3441.863,"duration":3.55}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":3441.863,"stop":3442.282,"duration":0.42}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"No way to prove it one way or the other.","start":3442.282,"stop":3444.106,"duration":1.82}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":3444.106,"stop":3445.234,"duration":1.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I was just wondering certainly that would not make any difference to us here for our observation but certainly the state must have that vial if that was in, wouldn't they, at this time while the case is still pending?","start":3445.234,"stop":3465.19,"duration":19.96},{"text":"They had it on the habeas corpus proceeding, certainly they must have it now.","start":3465.19,"stop":3469.264,"duration":4.07},{"text":"They wouldn't --","start":3469.264,"stop":3469.914,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They did --","start":3469.914,"stop":3470.215,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- have destroyed it, would they?","start":3470.215,"stop":3472.156,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I beg to differ with you, I do not think they had it at the habeas corpus proceeding.","start":3472.156,"stop":3476.298,"duration":4.14},{"text":"If they had it, it would now be on the record.","start":3476.298,"stop":3478.597,"duration":2.3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh!","start":3478.597,"stop":3479.478,"duration":0.88},{"text":"Pardon me, I understood that from the counsel that it was there.","start":3479.478,"stop":3484.131,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"No, it was not, Your Honor.","start":3484.131,"stop":3485.645,"duration":1.51},{"text":"The reason that it was not, I assume, it's because was never introduced into evidence at the trial.","start":3485.645,"stop":3489.449,"duration":3.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I see.","start":3489.449,"stop":3489.739,"duration":0.29}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"So there was -- it was not given that significance.","start":3489.739,"stop":3492.982,"duration":3.24}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I just misunderstood what counsel said.","start":3492.982,"stop":3498.274,"duration":5.29}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We turn then to the aspect of Brady versus Maryland that requires a -- Brady versus Maryland says that nondisclosure upon request constitutes a violation of due process.","start":3498.274,"stop":3510.454,"duration":12.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But you don't think it's significant within Brady and Maryland there was in fact a request?","start":3510.454,"stop":3519.6,"duration":9.15}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, in the light of this case --","start":3519.6,"stop":3523.706,"duration":4.11}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but please answer the question.","start":3523.706,"stop":3526.471,"duration":2.76}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon, excuse me.","start":3526.471,"stop":3527.555,"duration":1.08}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"You do or don't consider it significant that there was in Brady and Maryland in fact they request?","start":3527.555,"stop":3532.415,"duration":4.86}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor, I consider that that's significant.","start":3532.415,"stop":3533.346,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":3533.346,"stop":3537.537,"duration":4.19}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you have to say about the request that we made in this case for an opportunity to examine the evidence?","start":3537.537,"stop":3544.826,"duration":7.29}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I submit Your Honor that it was too broad to meet the requirements of Brady versus Maryland.","start":3544.826,"stop":3553.991,"duration":9.16},{"text":"All it said in the request itself Your Honor is found at page 2 of the Volume 4 of the record.","start":3553.991,"stop":3567.689,"duration":13.7},{"text":"Now, comes the defendant, Lloyd Eldon Miller, by William Malmgren, his attorney, hereby moves the Court to make an order permitting the defendant to make, or cause to be made, upon such terms and conditions as the Court may seem necessary to adequately insure the interests of the parties, a scientific examination of the physical evidence to be introduced by the people in this cause, etcetera.","start":3567.689,"stop":3585.735,"duration":18.05},{"text":"Now, even under Rule 16 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure, Your Honor, in order to make a -- for the defendant to make a motion to examine physical evidence in the hands of the government, it is necessary that they show the materiality and the reasonableness.","start":3585.735,"stop":3607.894,"duration":22.16},{"text":"I submit to Your Honors that this motion would not be -- would be held as improper under Rule 16 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure.","start":3607.894,"stop":3614.989,"duration":7.1}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"What they're asking here was for the physical evidence that it is going to be introduced by the people in this cause.","start":3614.989,"stop":3622.313,"duration":7.32},{"text":"And presumably that means that will give the state latitude to say, “Alright, we're going to have to use this, this and this and you can get it and make physical examination of it.”","start":3622.313,"stop":3637.926,"duration":15.61},{"text":"So what's the deficiency under Rule 16 or otherwise?","start":3637.926,"stop":3644.186,"duration":6.26}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think that they have shown either the materiality or the reasonableness, Your Honor.","start":3644.186,"stop":3648.118,"duration":3.93},{"text":"Now, one thing that is to be noted with respect to that motion is that they ask for the evidence that the state is going to introduce.","start":3648.118,"stop":3656.005,"duration":7.89},{"text":"The hair wasn't even introduced as very technically interpreted.","start":3656.005,"stop":3660.665,"duration":4.66},{"text":"The motion does not even apply to the hair.","start":3660.665,"stop":3662.677,"duration":2.01}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that, but it does apply to this part of the case involving the shorts.","start":3662.677,"stop":3669.932,"duration":7.25}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor, it does.","start":3669.932,"stop":3674.398,"duration":4.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And how at this particular time would the defense have known what the prosecution was going to introduce by way of physical evidence?","start":3674.398,"stop":3685.905,"duration":11.51}]},{"speakerName":"Maurice Rosenfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I assume that they -- the only way I can answer that question Your Honor is that they were given the right to view all the physical evidence in the case.","start":3685.905,"stop":3695.697,"duration":9.79},{"text":"He made that motion.","start":3695.697,"stop":3697.079,"duration":1.38},{"text":"They were allowed to go in.","start":3697.079,"stop":3698.37,"duration":1.29},{"text":"They were allowed to view all the physical evidence in the case.","start":3698.37,"stop":3702.742,"duration":4.37},{"text":"Now, they could've based -- the hair was seen of record that they saw the hairs when they made that view.","start":3702.742,"stop":3712.213,"duration":9.47},{"text":"A motion -- in addition of the fact, that the defense knew that the hair was found in the vagina of the victim, knew that hair of petitioner was taken for comparison purposes.","start":3712.213,"stop":3725.913,"duration":13.7},{"text":"I do not submit that it is too great a burden on the prosecution -- on the defense.","start":3725.913,"stop":3729.326,"duration":3.41},{"text":"I beg your pardon, to make a motion for their result of that examination.","start":3729.326,"stop":3734.917,"duration":5.59}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you say Mr. Michael that among the things they did see was the actual hair taken from the shorts?","start":3734.917,"stop":3741.816,"duration":6.9}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The testimony, Your Honors, states that amongst the physical evidence seen was hair and hairs.","start":3741.816,"stop":3749.618,"duration":7.8},{"text":"It does not define determining further, yes.","start":3749.618,"stop":3751.66,"duration":2.04}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That would identify them as including that the hair was --","start":3751.66,"stop":3755.246,"duration":3.59}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct, Your Honor.","start":3755.246,"stop":3756.274,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, hair was in the vial, wasn't it?","start":3756.274,"stop":3761.1,"duration":4.83}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The testimony does not state how it was, Your Honor.","start":3761.1,"stop":3764.14,"duration":3.04},{"text":"All it states is that “What evidence did you see when you examined it?”","start":3764.14,"stop":3767.842,"duration":3.7},{"text":"“I saw hairs.”","start":3767.842,"stop":3769.452,"duration":1.61},{"text":"He stated it, he didn't state whether it was in vial or how it was.","start":3769.452,"stop":3772.284,"duration":2.83},{"text":"I assumed it was in the vial because that at least was the way it went to the chemist.","start":3772.284,"stop":3775.933,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was the time they saw that after they made this motion?","start":3775.933,"stop":3782.177,"duration":6.24}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"First they --","start":3782.177,"stop":3782.198,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"After they made motion on page 2, was that when they saw the physical --?","start":3782.198,"stop":3787.809,"duration":5.61}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"As I read the record Your Honor, first they were allowed to view the evidence personally.","start":3787.809,"stop":3794.041,"duration":6.23},{"text":"Then they made the motion --","start":3794.041,"stop":3795.396,"duration":1.36}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"When?","start":3795.396,"stop":3797.957,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"They made the motion to view the evidence as I read it prior to the motion to make the scientific examination of the evidence.","start":3797.957,"stop":3806.761,"duration":8.8}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And were allowed to look at it?","start":3806.761,"stop":3808.324,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"They were, Your Honor.","start":3808.324,"stop":3809.288,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And then they made the motion for the (Voice Overlap).","start":3809.288,"stop":3811.189,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":3811.189,"stop":3813.375,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And that was the one that was denied?","start":3813.375,"stop":3814.821,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":3814.821,"stop":3815.341,"duration":0.52}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Was the original motion granted is that it for defense?","start":3815.341,"stop":3819.511,"duration":4.17}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I am not aware, Your Honor, whether it was just granted by the prosecution or whether there was a court order on that.","start":3819.511,"stop":3825.877,"duration":6.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Court make -- state any reason as to why it was denying him a right to examine?","start":3825.877,"stop":3833.35,"duration":7.47}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The Court does not.","start":3833.35,"stop":3834.95,"duration":1.6},{"text":"The -- in the Court the state's attorney was asked why he opposed that motion, and he testified Your Honor that he opposed it because they -- he could not be assured.","start":3834.95,"stop":3847.659,"duration":12.71},{"text":"He was not assured that the evidence would not be -- the chain of evidence would not be some way destroyed by the tests that were going to be taken.","start":3847.659,"stop":3855.492,"duration":7.83},{"text":"That is why he opposed it, the reason -- the ruling of the judge, however, is not in the record.","start":3855.492,"stop":3856.627,"duration":1.13},{"text":"The reason or the ruling of the judge is not in the record, Your Honor.","start":3856.627,"stop":3874.629,"duration":18},{"text":"We turn then Your Honors to the question of the bloody shorts.","start":3874.629,"stop":3882.328,"duration":7.7},{"text":"Now, the chemist for the state literally testified at the trial -- testified at the trial that the shorts did contain blood.","start":3882.328,"stop":3897.256,"duration":14.93},{"text":"And the state's attorney also testified -- stated in argument referred to these shorts as bloody shorts.","start":3897.256,"stop":3907.179,"duration":9.92},{"text":"Now, at the District Court in the habeas corpus proceeding --","start":3907.179,"stop":3912.049,"duration":4.87}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask before you get to the District Court.","start":3912.049,"stop":3915.597,"duration":3.55},{"text":"If the prosecuting attorney describe the blood that was on them or the amount of it, or did he make any representation as to whether this is blood on the shorts?","start":3915.597,"stop":3931.026,"duration":15.43}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I do not think the record indicated that he pointed to any spot, Your Honor.","start":3931.026,"stop":3934.156,"duration":3.13},{"text":"It said this is blood.","start":3934.156,"stop":3934.961,"duration":0.8},{"text":"He referred to the document in general as the bloody shorts.","start":3934.961,"stop":3937.994,"duration":3.03}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there are more than spots on that.","start":3937.994,"stop":3941.367,"duration":3.37}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":3941.367,"stop":3942.099,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"It's covered with something which they now say is paint.","start":3942.099,"stop":3945.875,"duration":3.78},{"text":"And I wonder if was that represented to the jury in any way as being the blood stained shorts without distinguishing --","start":3945.875,"stop":3959.944,"duration":14.07}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No statement was made to the jury Your Honor, as far as I know that there was any paint on these.","start":3959.944,"stop":3964.552,"duration":4.61},{"text":"There was then therefore, the jury would, I assume allow to draw the inference that all the spots were those of blood.","start":3964.552,"stop":3972.056,"duration":7.5},{"text":"On the other hand, I do not think any direct statement was made any given spot or all spots were blood.","start":3972.056,"stop":3979.27,"duration":7.21}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"When did the question first come up about the paint?","start":3979.27,"stop":3982.376,"duration":3.11}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"As far as I know Your Honor, in the District Court they did make a scientific examination of all the evidence.","start":3982.376,"stop":3990.409,"duration":8.03},{"text":"One Martin, a chemist employed by the petitioner here, took 12 strands at out of the more heavily stained areas of that garment, 12 fibers.","start":3990.409,"stop":4006.114,"duration":15.7},{"text":"He examined those 12 fibers, each out of one of the heavily stained areas.","start":4006.114,"stop":4010.084,"duration":3.97},{"text":"His testimony was that ten of the fibers contained paint.","start":4010.084,"stop":4015.272,"duration":5.19},{"text":"One of the fibers are kind of a carbon substance and one of the fibers an unidentified substance.","start":4015.272,"stop":4023.284,"duration":8.01}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael, when the shorts were introduced at the trial, did the defense make a motion at that time that they be permitted to have a scientific examination of it?","start":4023.284,"stop":4038.294,"duration":15.01}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"As far as I know Your Honor, and I think this is correct, the only motion from the scientific examination was the one that we have referred to with respect to --","start":4038.294,"stop":4044.813,"duration":6.52}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright, now try to get at the theory of this case.","start":4044.813,"stop":4048.999,"duration":4.19},{"text":"Suppose at the trial, the state offers the shorts and testimony is to be offered or is being or has been offered to the effect that those are blood stains.","start":4048.999,"stop":4064.306,"duration":15.31},{"text":"The defense then moves in an appropriate way to be given the opportunity to have a scientific examination of the shorts.","start":4064.306,"stop":4077.392,"duration":13.09},{"text":"In Illinois law, what would happen?","start":4077.392,"stop":4082.469,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Generally speaking, I would submit that it would be granted, Your Honor.","start":4082.469,"stop":4085.216,"duration":2.75},{"text":"The general rule under Illinois law is that, it was enunciated by the Court by the way in reviewing this case, is that there is a qualified -- red-light lining to the discretion of the Court to allow the defense to make scientific evidence of the --","start":4085.216,"stop":4101.832,"duration":16.62}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose the trial judge said in all this, “No, I won't let you do that.”","start":4101.832,"stop":4106.77,"duration":4.94},{"text":"Would that be an error under Illinois law?","start":4106.77,"stop":4110.216,"duration":3.45}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If there were no further basis than that Your Honor, I submit that yes it would be.","start":4110.216,"stop":4113.786,"duration":3.57}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought you said there was discretion on it?","start":4113.786,"stop":4116.229,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It could be reviewed however for abuse of discretion.","start":4116.229,"stop":4118.819,"duration":2.59}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"You think it would be introduced as discretion?","start":4118.819,"stop":4120.443,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would if there were no reason at all for denying a motion to make scientific evidence, I would submit that it would be in abuse of discretion.","start":4120.443,"stop":4126.144,"duration":5.7}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Why, because it's a denial of fair trial?","start":4126.144,"stop":4129.295,"duration":3.15}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":4129.295,"stop":4130.144,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well why, that's constitutional principle too, isn't it?","start":4130.144,"stop":4135.225,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"To the extent that Brady versus Maryland so enunciates it, yes sir.","start":4135.225,"stop":4143.01,"duration":7.78}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did -- may I ask this, did the report of the state's experts who examined these shorts report that the major portion of what's on there is paint?","start":4143.01,"stop":4157.413,"duration":14.4}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The report of the state's expert on that Your Honor was that he had examined it, he had found paint and he made no -- I take it back, he had found blood and he made no test for any other substance.","start":4157.413,"stop":4170.639,"duration":13.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And he made no reference in his report that the -- that what is so observable there is paint and not blood?","start":4170.639,"stop":4178.457,"duration":7.82}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The chemist did not, Your Honor.","start":4178.457,"stop":4179.982,"duration":1.52},{"text":"The state's attorney in the District Court did testify that he knew that all of the stains on it were not blood.","start":4179.982,"stop":4185.31,"duration":5.33},{"text":"That is all we have in the record on that issue.","start":4185.31,"stop":4187.938,"duration":2.63}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"He knew that at the time that the shorts was introduced in evidence?","start":4187.938,"stop":4190.376,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He so testified in the District Court, Your Honor.","start":4190.376,"stop":4192.438,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But he didn't disclose that time?","start":4192.438,"stop":4194.536,"duration":2.1}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He did not, Your Honor.","start":4194.536,"stop":4195.309,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"You know whether in summation he used the garment in his summation to the jury?","start":4195.309,"stop":4202.168,"duration":6.86}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He certainly referred to the bloody shots.","start":4202.168,"stop":4203.957,"duration":1.79},{"text":"Of course, the report of the short hand report, it would not indicate whether he was waiving it or --","start":4203.957,"stop":4208.262,"duration":4.3}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But at the time he made reference to it.","start":4208.262,"stop":4210.094,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He did, Your Honor.","start":4210.094,"stop":4211.037,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"He knew that there was -- that at least all of the spots were not blood but some or something else.","start":4211.037,"stop":4215.676,"duration":4.64}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":4215.676,"stop":4216.258,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And said nothing about it.","start":4216.258,"stop":4217.277,"duration":1.02}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":4217.277,"stop":4218.393,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Where does that -- I want to be sure he's sure what he did admit it to his knowledge at the time of -- at the clemency hearing or at the habeas corpus hearing --","start":4218.393,"stop":4228.497,"duration":10.1}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"At the habeas corpus --","start":4228.497,"stop":4229.183,"duration":0.69}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- he admitted as to his knowledge at the time of the trial that some of the stains, that at least some of the stains were not blood.","start":4229.183,"stop":4236.077,"duration":6.89}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Volume 2, Your Honor, page 581.","start":4236.077,"stop":4239.357,"duration":3.28}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Volume 2, page 581.","start":4239.357,"stop":4244.725,"duration":5.37},{"text":"Well, this -- is this the prosecuting attorney at the trial who's testifying?","start":4244.725,"stop":4250.262,"duration":5.54}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I beg to change that to make it 580, Your Honor.","start":4250.262,"stop":4253.834,"duration":3.57}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"580?","start":4253.834,"stop":4255.731,"duration":1.9},{"text":"This is Blaine Ramsey?","start":4255.731,"stop":4257.665,"duration":1.93}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"This is Blaine Ramsey, yes Your Honor, at the bottom of the page.","start":4257.665,"stop":4261.025,"duration":3.36},{"text":"“Let me ask you this Mr. Ramsey.","start":4261.025,"stop":4263.423,"duration":2.4},{"text":"As a matter of fact Mr. Ramsey didn't you know at the time of the trial Lloyd Eldon Miller Jr., that these spots in this examination were not blood?”","start":4263.423,"stop":4269.912,"duration":6.49},{"text":"“Oh!","start":4269.912,"stop":4270.111,"duration":0.2},{"text":"I knew that all of them were not blood, yes sir.”","start":4270.111,"stop":4281.702,"duration":11.59}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what you were referring to the --","start":4281.702,"stop":4282.416,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I was.","start":4282.416,"stop":4283.864,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":4283.864,"stop":4284.854,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Then he said also, “With regard to those that can be seen by the naked eye, you knew at the time of trial, didn't you, that those spots that could be seen by the naked eye were not blood spots.","start":4284.854,"stop":4299.269,"duration":14.41},{"text":"You knew that, didn't you?”","start":4299.269,"stop":4300.865,"duration":1.6},{"text":"“Well not conclusively.","start":4300.865,"stop":4303.047,"duration":2.18},{"text":"I had knowledge from a chemist that there was blood on it.”","start":4303.047,"stop":4306.507,"duration":3.46}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":4306.507,"stop":4307.02,"duration":0.51}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I see that's his further testimony.","start":4307.02,"stop":4309.856,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michaels, who was Mr. Litterly?","start":4309.856,"stop":4312.238,"duration":2.38}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He was a chemist, Your Honor, employed by the state bureau of -- I don't really -- criminal -- the scientific arm of the state government at that time.","start":4312.238,"stop":4322.957,"duration":10.72}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What about the statement on his testimony at 581.","start":4322.957,"stop":4326.299,"duration":3.34},{"text":"“Now as to those spots which you knew were not blood, what did you know those to be?","start":4326.299,"stop":4331.139,"duration":4.84},{"text":"What did you know of those Mr. Ramsey?”","start":4331.139,"stop":4333.38,"duration":2.24},{"text":"“I'm trying to recollect that.","start":4333.38,"stop":4334.962,"duration":1.58},{"text":"They said there was also paint on that I think that is remembered only.”","start":4334.962,"stop":4339.844,"duration":4.88},{"text":"“Who said it was paint?”","start":4339.844,"stop":4341.578,"duration":1.73},{"text":"“I presume Mr. Litterly but I really do not recall.”","start":4341.578,"stop":4345.687,"duration":4.11},{"text":"Is that -- are we to get -- take from this that he's suggesting that at the time it was offered at trial, he knew more of then that there were some spots were not blood, he knew that there were spots that were paint, is that it?","start":4345.687,"stop":4358.992,"duration":13.31}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"He testified there Your Honor that he knew that some of those spots were paint, I would assume.","start":4358.992,"stop":4363.589,"duration":4.6}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But Litterly testified at the trial that he didn't make test on the non-blood.","start":4363.589,"stop":4367.738,"duration":4.15}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Right, Your Honor.","start":4367.738,"stop":4368.233,"duration":0.49},{"text":"He testified only that he had examined for blood and he had made no other tests on the garment.","start":4368.233,"stop":4372.883,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But in order to -- he tested for blood but he didn't find blood in some of those spots.","start":4372.883,"stop":4381.43,"duration":8.55},{"text":"At least that is a fair reading of his testimony.","start":4381.43,"stop":4385.251,"duration":3.82},{"text":"He knew that some of the stains were not blood, so he did test the stains for blood.","start":4385.251,"stop":4397.491,"duration":12.24},{"text":"And if the prosecuting attorney knew at the time that some of the stains were not blood, the only source of information could be from Mr. Litterly, I presume.","start":4397.491,"stop":4406.779,"duration":9.29}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I would assume that that would be correct.","start":4406.779,"stop":4408.245,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And his source of information would I assume be a written report?","start":4408.245,"stop":4414.871,"duration":6.63}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The written report from Litterly is in the record, and at my recollection of it, it is in the echo -- the report of the exhibits.","start":4414.871,"stop":4427.666,"duration":12.8},{"text":"The report of Litterly is found at --","start":4427.666,"stop":4430.502,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"This is not the trial, isn't it?","start":4430.502,"stop":4432.353,"duration":1.85}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No this is the exhibits from the habeas corpus proceeding, Your Honor.","start":4432.353,"stop":4434.383,"duration":2.03}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Habeas corpus.","start":4434.383,"stop":4438.32,"duration":3.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it's number six, Your Honor I'm looking at it now to verify it.","start":4438.32,"stop":4441.966,"duration":3.65},{"text":"Yes, it is petitioner's exhibit number six.","start":4441.966,"stop":4445.341,"duration":3.38}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"This is what the prosecuting attorney knew?","start":4445.341,"stop":4449.986,"duration":4.64}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":4449.986,"stop":4454.256,"duration":4.27}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Where -- which one of these items applies to the --","start":4454.256,"stop":4467.047,"duration":12.79}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The reproduction is not very good.","start":4467.047,"stop":4469.406,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, it isn't Your Honor.","start":4469.406,"stop":4471.025,"duration":1.62},{"text":"I'm trying to Your Honor, I'm -- do you have one of your first?","start":4471.025,"stop":4484.263,"duration":13.24},{"text":"Yes, that's much better.","start":4484.263,"stop":4488.531,"duration":4.27}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I see some --","start":4488.531,"stop":4490.392,"duration":1.86}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It's -- at the next to last page, Your Honor.","start":4490.392,"stop":4493.651,"duration":3.26}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Can you read it?","start":4493.651,"stop":4494.706,"duration":1.06}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes I can from the original or much better copy of the report than you have available.","start":4494.706,"stop":4499.16,"duration":4.45}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"The pair of white jockey shorts?","start":4499.16,"stop":4500.903,"duration":1.74}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":4500.903,"stop":4501.627,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Described as number 17?","start":4501.627,"stop":4504.07,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Were examined by chemical means and found to be heavily stained with blood.","start":4504.07,"stop":4507.885,"duration":3.82},{"text":"Further serological examination include the blood was of human origin.","start":4507.885,"stop":4510.831,"duration":2.95},{"text":"It was probably of group A.","start":4510.831,"stop":4512.656,"duration":1.82},{"text":"Numerous hairs and fibers were herein to the shorts and were mounted in microscopic examination, a comparison of those hairs of pubic hairs 10 to 15 millimeters.","start":4512.656,"stop":4521.267,"duration":8.61},{"text":"Some similar characteristics, no definite opinions of whether or not the common origin is possible.","start":4521.267,"stop":4525.209,"duration":3.94},{"text":"One of the fibers found in the shorts was mounted and compared microscopically, samples of the fibers of the inner pant lining the color, size, etcetera.","start":4525.209,"stop":4532.836,"duration":7.63}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"No mention of paint at all.","start":4532.836,"stop":4534.033,"duration":1.2}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No mention of paint, Your Honor.","start":4534.033,"stop":4537.592,"duration":3.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, what page is that on do you say?","start":4537.592,"stop":4539.478,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"These are not numbered, Your Honor.","start":4539.478,"stop":4541.107,"duration":1.63},{"text":"This is exhibit number six, the next to the last page, Your Honor.","start":4541.107,"stop":4544.758,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, this -- there's no mention here that some of the stains were not blood.","start":4544.758,"stop":4550.188,"duration":5.43}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":4550.188,"stop":4551.484,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No there is not, Your Honor.","start":4551.484,"stop":4552.424,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then where did the prosecuting attorney get his information that some of the stains were not blood?","start":4552.424,"stop":4557.754,"duration":5.33}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I do not know, Your Honor.","start":4557.754,"stop":4558.551,"duration":0.8},{"text":"All I know is that in the District Court he --","start":4558.551,"stop":4559.624,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how about Mr. Litterly's testimony?","start":4559.624,"stop":4561.663,"duration":2.04},{"text":"He did testify that some of the stains were --","start":4561.663,"stop":4563.613,"duration":1.95}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":4563.613,"stop":4564.059,"duration":0.45},{"text":"He testified that he -- he did not testify that some of the stains were not.","start":4564.059,"stop":4566.422,"duration":2.36},{"text":"He testified that he knew that some of the stains were not blood.","start":4566.422,"stop":4570.085,"duration":3.66}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how about the testimony at the trial?","start":4570.085,"stop":4574.946,"duration":4.86}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Litterly's testimony at the trial you're referring to now, Your Honor?","start":4574.946,"stop":4579.008,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he then say -- he didn't make any mention at all as to other stains, did he, in his testimony?","start":4579.008,"stop":4585.82,"duration":6.81}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":4585.82,"stop":4586.665,"duration":0.85},{"text":"Litterly's testimony at the trial appears in the brown colored Volume 4 at page 168.","start":4586.665,"stop":4597.919,"duration":11.25}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Okay, thank you very much.","start":4597.919,"stop":4604.849,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It stated, “I examined and tested People's Exhibit 3 to determine the nature of the staining material thereon.","start":4604.849,"stop":4610.837,"duration":5.99},{"text":"That result of the first test was that this material upon the shorts is blood.","start":4610.837,"stop":4615.123,"duration":4.29},{"text":"I made a second examination it's as close as the blood of human origin and made a further examination which disclosed that the blood was of group A.”","start":4615.123,"stop":4622.839,"duration":7.72},{"text":"That was his testimony at that time.","start":4622.839,"stop":4623.763,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, now that -- he made more -- testify?","start":4623.763,"stop":4626.795,"duration":3.03}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Pardon me?","start":4626.795,"stop":4627.34,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"More fully did he, on the habeas corpus?","start":4627.34,"stop":4630.648,"duration":3.31},{"text":"Where was it that he finally conceded that some of the --","start":4630.648,"stop":4634.028,"duration":3.38}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not sure that he ever did.","start":4634.028,"stop":4635.382,"duration":1.35},{"text":"It was the state's attorney who conceded that he knew that some of the stains were not blood, Your Honor.","start":4635.382,"stop":4639.875,"duration":4.49}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the thing I referred to in form of my question.","start":4639.875,"stop":4641.098,"duration":1.22}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":4641.098,"stop":4641.926,"duration":0.83},{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":4641.926,"stop":4642.401,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I see.","start":4642.401,"stop":4648.906,"duration":6.51}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"We submit that on this issue, Your Honors, the critical point is whether there was blood on these shorts.","start":4648.906,"stop":4658.213,"duration":9.31},{"text":"The petitioner testified that he --","start":4658.213,"stop":4660.128,"duration":1.91}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, don't you think under a case like Napue against Illinois, the critical point is, even if there was blood on those shorts, a misrepresentation that the stains you could see there was blood when they knew it was -- if they knew it was paint.","start":4660.128,"stop":4677.504,"duration":17.38}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If there --","start":4677.504,"stop":4677.619,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Isn't that the knowing use of concept of misrepresentation by the prosecution in a criminal case?","start":4677.619,"stop":4684.56,"duration":6.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If there is blood on these shorts, Your Honor, and the mere testimony by the prosecution only is that there are -- is blood in these shorts.","start":4684.56,"stop":4690.944,"duration":6.38},{"text":"And if they do refer to them as bloody shorts, if there is blood on them, I submit that even though there's also paint, there is no going beyond the truth, if you will, as indicated by Napue.","start":4690.944,"stop":4702.799,"duration":11.85}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, as I understand it, today you can't find any blood on it?","start":4702.799,"stop":4706.35,"duration":3.55}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, Your Honor.","start":4706.35,"stop":4707.317,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"On what's in there.","start":4707.317,"stop":4708.246,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"However, the chemist for the prosecution did testify that he had no opinion today as to whether there was any blood on it or not.","start":4708.246,"stop":4714.647,"duration":6.4}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Today the appearance of those and the --","start":4714.647,"stop":4718.189,"duration":3.54}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Except for one stain, Your Honor that is unidentifiable in origin.","start":4718.189,"stop":4722.993,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Michaels as you held those up, I don't -- it hardly seems an unspotted -- look at that.","start":4722.993,"stop":4733.683,"duration":10.69}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"It --","start":4733.683,"stop":4734.308,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"If the blood has now disappeared, there's certainly an awful lot of paint.","start":4734.308,"stop":4739.538,"duration":5.23}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes there is, Your Honor.","start":4739.538,"stop":4741.306,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose the prosecutor had expressly represented to the jury that all of those spots were blood, would that have been your judgment, would that have been error under Illinois law?","start":4741.306,"stop":4761.783,"duration":20.48}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think not only under Illinois but under the decision of this Court it would have been, Your Honor.","start":4761.783,"stop":4765.365,"duration":3.58}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"That's because it would've not been consummate with our ideas of a fair trial.","start":4765.365,"stop":4770.275,"duration":4.91}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":4770.275,"stop":4771.292,"duration":1.02}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"So that what we have here is the variation in the sense that there was represented but there was blood on the shorts with no particularization of the exhibit, which was physically before the jury.","start":4771.292,"stop":4788.068,"duration":16.78},{"text":"It was not all blood but mostly paint as to the appearance to the naked eye now.","start":4788.068,"stop":4794.23,"duration":6.16}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":4794.23,"stop":4796.368,"duration":2.14},{"text":"However, I do want to go back to the point I was making with respect to Mr. Justice Stewart's question.","start":4796.368,"stop":4804.679,"duration":8.31},{"text":"The petitioner did testify in his confession, admitted in his confession that these were his shorts.","start":4804.679,"stop":4809.937,"duration":5.26},{"text":"The critical issue --","start":4809.937,"stop":4810.399,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Incidentally, where does this confession appear here, anywhere I can't --","start":4810.399,"stop":4814.416,"duration":4.02}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, it is in the record, Your Honor on before -- it appears really in two places.","start":4814.416,"stop":4822.978,"duration":8.56},{"text":"One, Mr. Christensen who took the confession, testified as to what he said to him during the interrogation and then another time that Mr. Baudino read his confession into the record.","start":4822.978,"stop":4833.893,"duration":10.91}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Where are the two places?","start":4833.893,"stop":4849.027,"duration":15.13}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Christensen's statement begins on 128, I believe it is, Your Honor.","start":4849.027,"stop":4858.974,"duration":9.95}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"That would be of Volume 1?","start":4858.974,"stop":4860.069,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"This would be the trial transcript, Your Honor, the brown covered by --","start":4860.069,"stop":4863.571,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Volume 4.","start":4863.571,"stop":4864.468,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Volume 4.","start":4864.468,"stop":4865.591,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"128.","start":4865.591,"stop":4875.803,"duration":10.21},{"text":"Sorry to take your time but I haven't --","start":4875.803,"stop":4877.699,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no.","start":4877.699,"stop":4884.955,"duration":7.26},{"text":"Then you have the -- we are looking now, Your Honor, for the -- where the confession.","start":4884.955,"stop":4896.014,"duration":11.06}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Right, thank you very much.","start":4896.014,"stop":4897.528,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any evidence in the record of about how that paint got on those shorts?","start":4897.528,"stop":4902.733,"duration":5.2}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, there's nothing at all, Your Honor, as far as I know.","start":4902.733,"stop":4905.218,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What was this man's occupation?","start":4905.218,"stop":4907.767,"duration":2.55}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you excuse me?","start":4907.767,"stop":4908.424,"duration":0.66},{"text":"The confession Your Honor of the defendant was right under the record of page 144.","start":4908.424,"stop":4916.115,"duration":7.69},{"text":"Pardon me, Your Honor?","start":4916.115,"stop":4917.03,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I asked, what was his occupation?","start":4917.03,"stop":4918.647,"duration":1.62},{"text":"As I recall it was evidence of him being a taxi driver.","start":4918.647,"stop":4921.471,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes there was, Your Honor.","start":4921.471,"stop":4921.967,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"He was not a painter.","start":4921.967,"stop":4923.02,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he was not, Your Honor.","start":4923.02,"stop":4925.843,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood there was some evidence in one of the proceedings to the effect that these shorts did not fit the defendant.","start":4925.843,"stop":4936.536,"duration":10.69},{"text":"Is there anything from the prosecution to rebut that?","start":4936.536,"stop":4941.116,"duration":4.58}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The testimony was, Your Honor, that the -- they would've been tight and uncomfortable if he had worn them.","start":4941.116,"stop":4949.317,"duration":8.2},{"text":"There's nothing to rebut that, Your Honor.","start":4949.317,"stop":4952.492,"duration":3.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any rebuttal of that?","start":4952.492,"stop":4954.057,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, there was not, Your Honor.","start":4954.057,"stop":4955.33,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Anything to show that the confirmation of the man had changed in the years that he was either fatter or thinner at the time this testimony was taken and at the time of the crime?","start":4955.33,"stop":4969.273,"duration":13.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"No, there was not, Your Honor.","start":4969.273,"stop":4975.346,"duration":6.07}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Perhaps I misunderstood.","start":4975.346,"stop":4976.426,"duration":1.08},{"text":"I thought you were starting to tell us at the time that I interrupted you to ask you where in the record the confession appeared.","start":4976.426,"stop":4982.677,"duration":6.25},{"text":"I thought you were trying to starting to tell us that in his confession, he admitted that those shorts were his?","start":4982.677,"stop":4988.135,"duration":5.46}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, he did Your Honor, in his confession.","start":4988.135,"stop":4990.747,"duration":2.61},{"text":"He later denied it.","start":4990.747,"stop":4992.144,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"But he never made any confession.","start":4992.144,"stop":4993.62,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but in his confession he admitted that the shorts were his.","start":4993.62,"stop":4996.574,"duration":2.95},{"text":"And so I submit that the relevant question is whether they did contain blood.","start":4996.574,"stop":5000.571,"duration":4},{"text":"If they did contain blood, this was the critical point.","start":5000.571,"stop":5005.86,"duration":5.29},{"text":"The presence of paint in addition to the blood, I respectfully submit, was immaterial.","start":5005.86,"stop":5011.356,"duration":5.5}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where did they get the shorts, from him?","start":5011.356,"stop":5014.064,"duration":2.71}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"They found -- a policeman found them in a old abandoned apartment building which was referred to at that time as the Van Buren Flats.","start":5014.064,"stop":5025.388,"duration":11.32},{"text":"In his confession, he stated that he had discarded them in the Van Buren Flats, but if I remember the testimony correctly, the police had found it before his confession if I'm not mistaken on that point.","start":5025.388,"stop":5037.529,"duration":12.14}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry must have read them -- perhaps I read it too quickly.","start":5037.529,"stop":5041.424,"duration":3.89},{"text":"This is the confession at page 145?","start":5041.424,"stop":5044.707,"duration":3.28}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":5044.707,"stop":5045.614,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"147, can you refer me to the admission that these particular shorts were his?","start":5045.614,"stop":5053.771,"duration":8.16},{"text":"I see that there is -- he states that he removed the shorts, but I don't find any --","start":5053.771,"stop":5060.547,"duration":6.78}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Perhaps it was in the statement of Mr. Christensen sir.","start":5060.547,"stop":5063.37,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I see.","start":5063.37,"stop":5065.054,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If you don't find it there.","start":5065.054,"stop":5066.618,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't find it in the confession.","start":5066.618,"stop":5071.121,"duration":4.5}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I found -- I find on a page 130 that he said he did this -- discard his shorts at Van Buren Flats, but that doesn't -- that's not the same as saying that those shorts are his.","start":5071.121,"stop":5088.741,"duration":17.62}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree with that, Your Honor.","start":5088.741,"stop":5092.911,"duration":4.17},{"text":"My recollection from the record is that he was shown the flats and he stated that they were -- I maybe in error on that.","start":5092.911,"stop":5098.998,"duration":6.09},{"text":"It was my recollection from reading the record, Your Honor.","start":5098.998,"stop":5102.15,"duration":3.15}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well he agreed that -- he conceded that they had been left at this place and they found these at that place.","start":5102.15,"stop":5107.899,"duration":5.75}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":5107.899,"stop":5108.602,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's probably might be accountable for your error.","start":5108.602,"stop":5111.216,"duration":2.61}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"That is --","start":5111.216,"stop":5111.565,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I find what you're referring to now, on page 132 just below the center of the page.","start":5111.565,"stop":5119.182,"duration":7.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael, I gather the impression from reading the phrase that the state in introducing the confession and the presentation of its case told the jury or left the impression with the jury that he have had obtained the confession of the defendant and then had verified it through these things and that they had found these things as a result of the confession.","start":5119.182,"stop":5155.136,"duration":35.95},{"text":"And I gather the impression also that there had been evidence later produced to show that they had these things before the confession and verify them by this confession.","start":5155.136,"stop":5171.536,"duration":16.4},{"text":"Now, did the state deny the latter?","start":5171.536,"stop":5175.13,"duration":3.59}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"As I remember that point, Your Honor, it's my understanding that the reading of the record that the items were found before the confession.","start":5175.13,"stop":5182.616,"duration":7.49}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":5182.616,"stop":5183.58,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Now --","start":5183.58,"stop":5183.912,"duration":0.33}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was that at any time represented to the jury that these things were found afterwards as a result of that confession?","start":5183.912,"stop":5192.856,"duration":8.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The petitioner has claimed that they are, Your Honor.","start":5192.856,"stop":5195.721,"duration":2.86},{"text":"As I read that section that he referred to, I was not -- I thought it was ambiguous which way they were referring to it.","start":5195.721,"stop":5201.517,"duration":5.8}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you have that citation recorded?","start":5201.517,"stop":5206.245,"duration":4.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Don't you think that's -- that might be important?","start":5206.245,"stop":5210.295,"duration":4.05}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If there were knowing misrepresentation to closing argument, I would say it would be very significant, Your Honor.","start":5210.295,"stop":5216.581,"duration":6.29},{"text":"If there was no evidence, however, brought out that he deliberately misstated anything, it is possible that a mistake could occur in -- by prosecution in closing argument which would not be deliberate mistake and would not amount to constitutional proportions.","start":5216.581,"stop":5232.964,"duration":16.38}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But neither that an important thing, it seems to me, whether these things were found and developed as a result of the plain confession that he made or whether they had these things and before the confession and did not report it to the --","start":5232.964,"stop":5255.163,"duration":22.2}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"The argument that you are referring to, Your Honor, is on page 375 of the volume printed by this Court, Volume 4, Your Honor.","start":5255.163,"stop":5265.009,"duration":9.85},{"text":"And it relates to the jacket of my -- attorney for the petitioner in form where he relates --","start":5265.009,"stop":5271.447,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that, the upper part of the volume?","start":5271.447,"stop":5273.246,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"About the middle of the page I believe, Your Honor.","start":5273.246,"stop":5278.396,"duration":5.15},{"text":"They could not have known, but when they put it there to find, the jacket was found where he had said he had put it.","start":5278.396,"stop":5283.192,"duration":4.8},{"text":"Words are about the middle of the page, Your Honor.","start":5283.192,"stop":5286.943,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"275?","start":5286.943,"stop":5288.253,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your -- 375, I beg your pardon.","start":5288.253,"stop":5291.526,"duration":3.27}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the one they could not have known, but when they went there to find the jacket it was found --","start":5291.526,"stop":5296.299,"duration":4.77}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":5296.299,"stop":5296.371,"duration":0.07}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- where he said he put it.","start":5296.371,"stop":5298.117,"duration":1.75}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":5298.117,"stop":5319.06,"duration":20.94},{"text":"We turn then Your Honors --","start":5319.06,"stop":5320.695,"duration":1.63}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, did -- is -- which is true, that they did find this thing after the confession or before?","start":5320.695,"stop":5329.606,"duration":8.91}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"My understanding of the record is that they found it before the confession, Your Honor.","start":5329.606,"stop":5332.571,"duration":2.97}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And that this, while it might not have been with intention to deceive, but was, untrue?","start":5332.571,"stop":5341.257,"duration":8.69}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"If that is -- as I read that, Your Honor, I am not absolutely clear just what the meaning of it.","start":5341.257,"stop":5347.346,"duration":6.09},{"text":"If you interpret that as saying that we took his -- what he told us and went out and there we found it then it would be untrue, yes Your Honor.","start":5347.346,"stop":5355.214,"duration":7.87}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":5355.214,"stop":5362.158,"duration":6.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"We turn then to the question of the advice to Mrs. Baxter that she had a right not to talk to the defense in this case.","start":5362.158,"stop":5377.599,"duration":15.44},{"text":"Now, Mrs. Baxter testified at the pardon and parole proceedings that she had been receiving many calls and was being bothered by the defense attorney and she was, in her words, perturbed.","start":5377.599,"stop":5395.743,"duration":18.14},{"text":"She called up the state's attorney and asked what the situation was.","start":5395.743,"stop":5400.234,"duration":4.49},{"text":"He told her in effect that, “You have a right not to talk to the defense if you want to.”","start":5400.234,"stop":5408.612,"duration":8.38},{"text":"This is corroborated by his own testimony at the District Court where he testified that he told other witnesses amongst her that by request that they had a right not to talk to the defense and they must make up their own mind whether they wanted to or not.","start":5408.612,"stop":5424.676,"duration":16.06},{"text":"Now, we submit that this statement is absolutely correct.","start":5424.676,"stop":5432.784,"duration":8.11},{"text":"Absent a subpoena to some particular hearing, every private individual has a right not only to talk not to the defense, but not to talk to the prosecution, absent an appropriate subpoena.","start":5432.784,"stop":5447.184,"duration":14.4},{"text":"We submit that there was absolutely no violation of any rights in respect to that statement.","start":5447.184,"stop":5455.295,"duration":8.11}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I was wondering about her testimony when it was offered and when the Court was asked for permission to permit her testimony as a court witness.","start":5455.295,"stop":5467.446,"duration":12.15},{"text":"The prosecution said they would consent to it only if her unreliability was conceded.","start":5467.446,"stop":5475.532,"duration":8.09},{"text":"Now, why would that -- is that a normal thing?","start":5475.532,"stop":5478.306,"duration":2.77}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Let me correct that statement.","start":5478.306,"stop":5479.858,"duration":1.55},{"text":"Just -- my understanding, Your Honor is with that the Court said that rather than the prosecution.","start":5479.858,"stop":5485.214,"duration":5.36},{"text":"The Court said, “If you will state to me that she is unreliable in some way, I will allow you to call her as a court's witness.","start":5485.214,"stop":5493.872,"duration":8.66},{"text":"If you do not so state then I will give you great latitude in asking leading questions and various examinations you want, but I will not call her as a court witness.”","start":5493.872,"stop":5503.006,"duration":9.13},{"text":"They then refused that offer -- they refused the Court's offer to have called her and have this great leeway in question -- with respect to leading questions.","start":5503.006,"stop":5514.137,"duration":11.13},{"text":"I assume they testified because they did not want to be bound by the testimony of someone whom they did not know who was going to testify.","start":5514.137,"stop":5521.48,"duration":7.34}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that a test of whether a person -- the defendant should be entitled to call a witness as the Court's witness that he must admit that there's some unreliability?","start":5521.48,"stop":5537.317,"duration":15.84}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it is -- the question is pretty much within the discretion of the Court, Your Honor.","start":5537.317,"stop":5542.709,"duration":5.39},{"text":"And I don't think it's subject to review for abuse in the same way as the scientific evidence was as I referred earlier to the question of Mr. Justice Fortas.","start":5542.709,"stop":5552.293,"duration":9.58},{"text":"I think that if the Court -- if you can show some reason to the Court why he should be called as the Court's witness, that he pretty well usually is.","start":5552.293,"stop":5562.219,"duration":9.93},{"text":"The Court, in exercise of its discretion in this case, merely believed that they had not shown sufficient grounds to exercise his discretion in that regard.","start":5562.219,"stop":5575.854,"duration":13.64},{"text":"We turn then to the question of the unreliable witness, Betty Baldwin, not Betty Baldwin-Curry.","start":5575.854,"stop":5585.833,"duration":9.98},{"text":"The prosecution -- the petitioner in this case contends that the prosecution was in error for calling that witness when they knew that she was unreliable.","start":5585.833,"stop":5602.842,"duration":17.01},{"text":"We submit, Your Honors, that there is absolutely no constitutional requirement that prohibits the calling of a witness, who in the past has not been believed if, and this is the big if, they do believe her testimony on this occasion.","start":5602.842,"stop":5620.14,"duration":17.3},{"text":"Now, on this occasion, the evidence is rather complete that at least two people so testified that they fully believed her on this occasion.","start":5620.14,"stop":5630.28,"duration":10.14},{"text":"On that basis, they called her and we believe that it is a proper to call a witness whose testimony you believe even though at some past occasion you may not have believed this witness' testimony.","start":5630.28,"stop":5641.569,"duration":11.29}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Which one would they believe?","start":5641.569,"stop":5642.724,"duration":1.15},{"text":"Which part of her testimony would they believe, for in the Court, she said she had known him for two years and prior to that time she had told the police that she knew him for five weeks?","start":5642.724,"stop":5655.204,"duration":12.48}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there is another factor in that regard, Your Honor.","start":5655.204,"stop":5659.15,"duration":3.95},{"text":"When -- if the she had told the police that she knew him at the time of the crime for five weeks.","start":5659.15,"stop":5664.825,"duration":5.68},{"text":"Now, this question was asked at the trial which was ten months after the crime.","start":5664.825,"stop":5670.995,"duration":6.17},{"text":"How long have you known him, not how long had you known him Your Honor, not how long had you known him at the time of the crime, but how long have you known him, which means from the present past.","start":5670.995,"stop":5681.294,"duration":10.3},{"text":"And I submit, Your Honor, that the correct answer to that would have been 11 months, because she had known him at the time that question was asked for 11 months.","start":5681.294,"stop":5692.05,"duration":10.76},{"text":"Now, I submit Your Honor, that to allow that to go unrefuted is absolutely immaterial.","start":5692.05,"stop":5697.924,"duration":5.87},{"text":"There is no materiality at all in this record to the significance of whether that she had known him 11 months or two years.","start":5697.924,"stop":5706.562,"duration":8.64},{"text":"The defendant states there is some materiality --","start":5706.562,"stop":5710.081,"duration":3.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have the citation to that, but don't take the time to look.","start":5710.081,"stop":5714.525,"duration":4.44},{"text":"If you don't know, don't bother.","start":5714.525,"stop":5717.752,"duration":3.23}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean as to the -- where as to the formal questioned asked?","start":5717.752,"stop":5720.185,"duration":2.43}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"As to whether they said, “How long have you known him?”","start":5720.185,"stop":5722.531,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes I have it right here, Your Honor, it's in Volume 2, -- Volume 2 page 702 at the top of the page.","start":5722.531,"stop":5734.38,"duration":11.85},{"text":"At the very top of the page, Your Honor, it refers “Do you know the defendant Lloyd Eldon Miller?”","start":5734.38,"stop":5739.784,"duration":5.4},{"text":"She said, “Yes sir.”","start":5739.784,"stop":5741.47,"duration":1.69},{"text":"“How long have you known him?”","start":5741.47,"stop":5743.561,"duration":2.09},{"text":"“Approximately two years.”","start":5743.561,"stop":5752.607,"duration":9.05},{"text":"The principle -- there is concluding that thought Your Honor also if there's a contention under Napue versus Illinois that they allowed knowing testimony to go in the record as they did not contradict that statement.","start":5752.607,"stop":5766.321,"duration":13.71},{"text":"There is absolutely no evidence in this record that they were aware of the statement was made.","start":5766.321,"stop":5770.009,"duration":3.69},{"text":"Now, there was the fact that that statement had been made to the prosecution, but there was no evidence that they had gone down that statement and checked every one of her answers against them, I'm sure they knew it in substance.","start":5770.009,"stop":5779.932,"duration":9.92},{"text":"But this was such a, I submit, immaterial point that they probably didn't even realize that she was violating the statement that they had given, or at least there's no evidence in the record that they had, Your Honor.","start":5779.932,"stop":5790.831,"duration":10.9}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Michael, may I ask you concerning this witness if it is the fact that they have concluded before this proceeding that this witness had made a false accusation against another person for a crime that she said he had confessed to her but was not true.","start":5790.831,"stop":5818.601,"duration":27.77},{"text":"And then also that she had made another one which was under investigation and which the experts found that it was inconclusive but they believed that she was not telling the truth and that the county authorities who prosecuted this case suggested that they discontinue the investigation of the truth of that statement until this case was tried so she could be a witness here.","start":5818.601,"stop":5853.661,"duration":35.06}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, what you say is very -- is in substance.","start":5853.661,"stop":5858.947,"duration":5.29},{"text":"Now, I know of only one prior occasion that she had made a story about another crime that was this narcotics story.","start":5858.947,"stop":5864.839,"duration":5.89},{"text":"With respect to that statement, she was given a lie detector test to check whether it was right.","start":5864.839,"stop":5870.027,"duration":5.19},{"text":"The result was inconclusive.","start":5870.027,"stop":5871.331,"duration":1.3},{"text":"They said that they found -- they did not believe her, although the test was inconclusive and that they were going to drop the matter.","start":5871.331,"stop":5881.354,"duration":10.02},{"text":"The only other instance that I can think of which talks to their -- to the unreliability relates to the statement that Mr. Malmgren, the attorney for the petitioner had tried to coerce this witness.","start":5881.354,"stop":5894.039,"duration":12.68},{"text":"Now, as far as I read the record in this case, those claims have never been disproving, Your Honor.","start":5894.039,"stop":5899.048,"duration":5.01}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood that there was an investigation of that, and the authorities indicated that they thought that was not true, but the people who prosecuted this case suggested that the investigation be discontinued until after the trial of this case.","start":5899.048,"stop":5920.986,"duration":21.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard A. Michael","textObjs":[{"text":"That was -- the statement that they believe was not true of hers related to the narcotics story, Your Honor.","start":5920.986,"stop":5926.018,"duration":5.03},{"text":"There was no evidence one way or another whether they believed the story with respect to the Attorney Malmgren.","start":5926.018,"stop":5931.204,"duration":5.19},{"text":"However, they did -- the statement -- the prosecution did say, “Let's not get that question out of this case so there'll be no question of prejudice,” you know, to the defendant by the fact that his attorney made the some question of improper statements to a prosecution witness.","start":5931.204,"stop":5949.358,"duration":18.15},{"text":"So that was how it all advanced and was either the last statement in the record on that Your Honor is that it either still pending or is been dismissed.","start":5949.358,"stop":5956.705,"duration":7.35},{"text":"I assume it has been dismissed, but there has never been a hearing on it.","start":5956.705,"stop":5958.189,"duration":1.48},{"text":"It has never been proved conclusively one way or another whether that allegation was correct or not.","start":5958.189,"stop":5965.062,"duration":6.87},{"text":"Thank you, Your Honors.","start":5965.062,"stop":5970.817,"duration":5.76}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Lassers.","start":5970.817,"stop":5973.916,"duration":3.1}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court.","start":5973.916,"stop":5977.45,"duration":3.53},{"text":"I believe that everything that we desire to say has been said, unless the Court has questions, I have nothing further.","start":5977.45,"stop":5988.011,"duration":10.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":5988.011,"stop":5988.696,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Can I ask you one last question?","start":5988.696,"stop":5990.42,"duration":1.72}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly.","start":5990.42,"stop":5991.303,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"In your petition for habeas corpus in the District Court, did you rely on the ground of coerced confession?","start":5991.303,"stop":6002.717,"duration":11.41}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Your Honor.","start":6002.717,"stop":6003.652,"duration":0.94},{"text":"My recollection is that we did.","start":6003.652,"stop":6005.642,"duration":1.99},{"text":"Yes, we did rely on that.","start":6005.642,"stop":6005.85,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, did the District Court rule on it or not?","start":6005.85,"stop":6011.308,"duration":5.46}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He ruled that it was not coerced, Mr. Justice White.","start":6011.308,"stop":6013.788,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Court of Appeals rule?","start":6013.788,"stop":6019.671,"duration":5.88}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I think they did.","start":6019.671,"stop":6020.632,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But at least you -- this is not the first time you've raised the issue of coerced confession in this Court, isn't it?","start":6020.632,"stop":6027.487,"duration":6.86}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"In this Court?","start":6027.487,"stop":6029.037,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"You've raised it below, on the preserved two points of the --","start":6029.037,"stop":6032.19,"duration":3.15}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, yes!","start":6032.19,"stop":6035.52,"duration":3.33}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":6035.52,"stop":6035.908,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":6035.908,"stop":6038.508,"duration":2.6}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - January 11, 1967","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren13/oral_argument_audio/15563","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 250, Lloyd Eldon Miller Jr. versus Frank J. Pate, Warden.","start":0,"stop":38.311,"duration":38.31},{"text":"Mr. Lassers.","start":38.311,"stop":39.995,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, this is a capital case that comes to this Court on habeas corpus.","start":39.995,"stop":58.298,"duration":18.3},{"text":"Relief was granted by the District Court of the Northern District of Illinois, Judge Perry, the state took an appeal and the Seventh Circuit reversed and this Court granted certiorari.","start":58.298,"stop":71.718,"duration":13.42},{"text":"There are four principal errors that we contend occurred in this trial and I'm going to try cover the four.","start":71.718,"stop":82.577,"duration":10.86},{"text":"The case is unique, Your Honors, and that the covenants on exonerating this petitioner of the crime was discovered even before the petitioner himself was arrested.","start":82.577,"stop":98.99,"duration":16.41},{"text":"The -- the petitioner was convicted of murder and on Saturday afternoon, November 26th, 1955 in Canton, Illinois at 4:00 in the afternoon and a little eight year old girl was found under a mining car severely injured but still living.","start":98.99,"stop":121.919,"duration":22.93},{"text":"She was rushed to a hospital where she dies at 5:47 P.M. that afternoon.","start":121.919,"stop":127.943,"duration":6.02},{"text":"At 6:20, while the body was still on the operating table, the coroner arrived and he performed an examination.","start":127.943,"stop":137.005,"duration":9.06},{"text":"Now, the coroner himself was a physician.","start":137.005,"stop":140.364,"duration":3.36},{"text":"In the course of that examination, he took a vaginal smear and there had been a sex attack on this child and he took the smear and the vaginal smear was sealed in a vial with a surgical tape and this smear together with a mass of other evidence was immediately taken to Springfield which was few miles away and it was taken to the state crime laboratory there.","start":140.364,"stop":174.615,"duration":34.25},{"text":"When it arrived there, the man in-charge, a man by the name of Forest literally, had found the vial and it was still sealed and it had on it Janice May, the name of the victim and the date of the crime November 26th, 1955 and the initials of the coroner.","start":174.615,"stop":199.262,"duration":24.65},{"text":"He opened the vial and inside was a tissue which he examined.","start":199.262,"stop":205.113,"duration":5.85},{"text":"And when he made a close examination, he found that there was a single strand of hair that was adhering to the tissue.","start":205.113,"stop":217.17,"duration":12.06},{"text":"The petitioner Lloyd Eldon Miller was arrested the following day on November the 29th, at about six o'clock -- no about eight o'clock in the evening, on a Monday.","start":217.17,"stop":230.344,"duration":13.17},{"text":"The crime took place on Saturday and he was arrested on Monday.","start":230.344,"stop":234.445,"duration":4.1},{"text":"He was immediately taken to Springfield which was the same place for the state crime laboratory was located and he -- they took him up to the crime laboratory and they took blood sample and this and that and other things and among -- there are other examinations, they took a sample of his pubic hairs.","start":234.445,"stop":253.711,"duration":19.27},{"text":"And immediately after that, on the night of the November the 29th, they had an extensive period of interrogation which lasted I believe until one in the morning.","start":253.711,"stop":264.04,"duration":10.33},{"text":"He was taken back to his cell on the following night, the night of the 30th, there was another extensive period of examination and he signed a confession shortly after midnight on Wednesday evening which was the second night of the examination.","start":264.04,"stop":281.444,"duration":17.4},{"text":"Now, he was tried in Carthage Illinois, in September of 1956 and which was about eight months -- ten months afterwards.","start":281.444,"stop":293.688,"duration":12.24},{"text":"And in May, which was several months before the -- before the trial, the -- his then defense attorneys, we were not representing him at the time, filed a motion on the trial court asking, I believe, to make a physical examination of the evidence.","start":293.688,"stop":313.274,"duration":19.59},{"text":"And the state came in and they resisted that, and the trial court denied the motion, and they preserved the error in the record and the Supreme Court of Illinois affirmed the denial of the right to make a physical examination of the evidence and the -- they affirmed the conviction.","start":313.274,"stop":336.795,"duration":23.52}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Specifically what evidence?","start":336.795,"stop":338.272,"duration":1.48},{"text":"What -- what evidence did he want physically to examine?","start":338.272,"stop":342.756,"duration":4.48}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there was --","start":342.756,"stop":342.805,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The vial?","start":342.805,"stop":345.195,"duration":2.39}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- there was a physical evidence that was later introduced to the trial.","start":345.195,"stop":351.594,"duration":6.4},{"text":"I don't think that they knew themselves exactly what physical evidence there was.","start":351.594,"stop":356.225,"duration":4.63},{"text":"But there were various -- there was a -- that there was a pair of shorts which we can talk about later on.","start":356.225,"stop":361.083,"duration":4.86}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I just wondered whether the motion referred to anything specific or just generally asked permission to examine all physical evidence.","start":361.083,"stop":370.755,"duration":9.67}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe that is correct.","start":370.755,"stop":371.953,"duration":1.2},{"text":"I assume that's right.","start":371.953,"stop":372.888,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the hair a part of evidence in the trial?","start":372.888,"stop":376.079,"duration":3.19}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not Your Honor, no.","start":376.079,"stop":379.063,"duration":2.98},{"text":"Now, the record -- what?","start":379.063,"stop":380.928,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Offered?","start":380.928,"stop":381.466,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not offered, no, no.","start":381.466,"stop":384.384,"duration":2.92},{"text":"Now, the petitioner --","start":384.384,"stop":386.558,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Could I ask -- could I ask you another question?","start":386.558,"stop":388.127,"duration":1.57}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":388.127,"stop":390.111,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any proof that he were at any stage in supplementary proceeding, or otherwise, that the pubic hair was actually found in the vagina?","start":390.111,"stop":400.31,"duration":10.2}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the record shows that the -- that the physician came and that we thought the vial was there and it have the initials of the coroner, it was still sealed, with the name of the child and the date of the crime, and that this was then sent to the crime laboratory, and that is the extent of the record.","start":400.31,"stop":423.64,"duration":23.33}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, the hair was in the vial?","start":423.64,"stop":425.867,"duration":2.23}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The hair was on -- was adhering to a tissue in the vial --","start":425.867,"stop":429.001,"duration":3.13}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"In the vial?","start":429.001,"stop":430.565,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But the person who actually took the smear never testified that he found a hair in the vagina?","start":430.565,"stop":439.051,"duration":8.49}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he did not.","start":439.051,"stop":440.143,"duration":1.09},{"text":"He have --","start":440.143,"stop":440.574,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And that's only an inference from the fact that the hair was in the vial?","start":440.574,"stop":449.551,"duration":8.98},{"text":"That -- that you think it came from the vagina at the time.","start":449.551,"stop":452.867,"duration":3.32}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice White, we think that the inference on that is just overwhelming.","start":452.867,"stop":456.616,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but wholly aside of how you characterized it, that's what it rest on.","start":456.616,"stop":460.302,"duration":3.69}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":460.302,"stop":461.843,"duration":1.54},{"text":"Now, the -- it is also a fact that this coroner did testify.","start":461.843,"stop":468.513,"duration":6.67},{"text":"He was called as a witness by the prosecution and he did testify and he said that when he arrived there, the girl was dead and I believe he said that she was still on the operating table.","start":468.513,"stop":480.083,"duration":11.57},{"text":"Now, the -- the counsel for the defendant at the time was permitted to physically to view the physical evidence on one occasion and he subsequently testified in subsequent proceedings.","start":480.083,"stop":497.379,"duration":17.3}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what does that mean?","start":497.379,"stop":498.342,"duration":0.96},{"text":"Allowed physically to view -- what's that?","start":498.342,"stop":501.364,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, he -- he went into the room and the evidence was put on a table before him and he with his co-counsel and they -- they looked.","start":501.364,"stop":512.654,"duration":11.29},{"text":"I don't know whether they were allowed to touch or not.","start":512.654,"stop":514.832,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how does that different from what they sought on --","start":514.832,"stop":517.517,"duration":2.69}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"What they sought was permission to have a scientific examination made which would involve bringing in specialists in various kinds --","start":517.517,"stop":526.554,"duration":9.04}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, did they see this after the motion was denied but before trial?","start":526.554,"stop":531.177,"duration":4.62}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe that's correct, Your Honor.","start":531.177,"stop":534.078,"duration":2.9},{"text":"Now, after they --","start":534.078,"stop":536.219,"duration":2.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they see what before -- before trial but after -- after their --","start":536.219,"stop":541.638,"duration":5.42}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They saw a pair of short, a jacket, and a rock, and --","start":541.638,"stop":551.455,"duration":9.82}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The vial?","start":551.455,"stop":552.524,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I think they saw the vial, yes.","start":552.524,"stop":555.735,"duration":3.21},{"text":"Now, it --","start":555.735,"stop":557.308,"duration":1.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was the hair observable?","start":557.308,"stop":559.95,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know -- I don't know whether the record shows whether it was or it was not.","start":559.95,"stop":565.3,"duration":5.35},{"text":"It may have been.","start":565.3,"stop":567.507,"duration":2.21},{"text":"Now --","start":567.507,"stop":567.983,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was it called to their attention that there was such a thing --","start":567.983,"stop":571.977,"duration":3.99}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The record --","start":571.977,"stop":571.994,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in the vial?","start":571.994,"stop":572.646,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The record does not show that it was ever called to their attention.","start":572.646,"stop":575.825,"duration":3.18},{"text":"However, the petitioner testified that he was showing a hair and I will come --","start":575.825,"stop":583.419,"duration":7.59}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"He was shown what?","start":583.419,"stop":583.607,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to that in just a moment.","start":583.607,"stop":585.904,"duration":2.3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"He was shown what?","start":585.904,"stop":587.002,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That he was shown a hair.","start":587.002,"stop":589.768,"duration":2.77},{"text":"During the course of his interrogation and this was on the second night and it was shortly before he signed a confession, he testified that he was shown a hair, that he was taken into a microscope room which is what he called it, and that he was told that one of his hairs matched the hair from the little -- that was found in the little girl and he said that that -- they told him that he could look at the microscope through himself and then he said that he informed the people present them hairs don't match.","start":589.768,"stop":631.671,"duration":41.9}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- that what?","start":631.671,"stop":632.594,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Them hairs don't match.","start":632.594,"stop":634.36,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- the petitioner's said that?","start":634.36,"stop":636.516,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, Your Honor and he -- he so testified at the -- at the hearing on the motion to admit the confession.","start":636.516,"stop":648.412,"duration":11.9}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well now, what did the -- the police concede that they had shown him a hair during the period that that is --","start":648.412,"stop":653.469,"duration":5.06}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"There was no denial of this.","start":653.469,"stop":654.98,"duration":1.51}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No denial?","start":654.98,"stop":656.449,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The record on the prosecution side assigned on that issue.","start":656.449,"stop":660.203,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But there's no concession that it was shown?","start":660.203,"stop":663.668,"duration":3.47}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It's silent.","start":663.668,"stop":664.995,"duration":1.33},{"text":"And I -- I think it's a fair to say that they have conceded, that they showed him the hair and that they told him that the hairs matched.","start":664.995,"stop":673.513,"duration":8.52}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, when was it -- how long after this was -- that was determined that in fact this was not a hair from his body?","start":673.513,"stop":680.664,"duration":7.15}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Eight years, Your Honor.","start":680.664,"stop":682.548,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Eight years from --","start":682.548,"stop":683.086,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Eight years, yes sir.","start":683.086,"stop":684.874,"duration":1.79},{"text":"It was -- then, what happened was after the affirmance --","start":684.874,"stop":689.305,"duration":4.43}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, when did the police first know that it was not a hair from his body?","start":689.305,"stop":695.18,"duration":5.88}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"At the very latest, on December the 7th of 1955 --","start":695.18,"stop":702.114,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That?","start":702.114,"stop":702.124,"duration":0.01}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"-- which was -- and we think it's a fair inference from the record that they knew it the very afternoon that the hair was delivered to the crime laboratory which was a day or two after the crime.","start":702.124,"stop":715.34,"duration":13.22}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in any event, at the time he was shown the hair and told that it was from his body, the police knew that in fact it was not from his body.","start":715.34,"stop":724.169,"duration":8.83}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the -- the -- we think that that is the inescapable inference from the record.","start":724.169,"stop":730.831,"duration":6.66}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what I'm trying to get to is, how do we know that police knew that it was not from his body at the time they told him it was?","start":730.831,"stop":739.692,"duration":8.86},{"text":"What in the record shows that?","start":739.692,"stop":741.022,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Only -- it's only the inference and based on this fact that the hair was already in the crime laboratory for over 24 hours at the time they made the false statement to him.","start":741.022,"stop":757.207,"duration":16.18}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It was there but I'm still uncertain how it is they knew it was not his.","start":757.207,"stop":762.123,"duration":4.92},{"text":"When was it determined and by whom was it determined that it was not a hair --","start":762.123,"stop":765.624,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was --","start":765.624,"stop":765.66,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- from his body?","start":765.66,"stop":766.544,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It was determined by his fellow literally in -- and he wrote up an official report --","start":766.544,"stop":774.481,"duration":7.94}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Is he in the crime laboratory?","start":774.481,"stop":775.682,"duration":1.2}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He is in the crime laboratory --","start":775.682,"stop":776.733,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":776.733,"stop":777.35,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"And he wrote an official report, one copy of which went to the prosecuting attorney --","start":777.35,"stop":782.567,"duration":5.22}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"In which he stated that it was not a hair from his body?","start":782.567,"stop":785.015,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":785.015,"stop":785.785,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, when was that report prepared?","start":785.785,"stop":787.558,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It is dated December the 7th, 1955.","start":787.558,"stop":791.14,"duration":3.58}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And how long -- on what dates was the interrogation?","start":791.14,"stop":795,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"On November the 29th and November the 30th.","start":795,"stop":799.003,"duration":4},{"text":"And the hair --","start":799.003,"stop":799.07,"duration":0.07}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And prior to the date of that report in any event?","start":799.07,"stop":801.474,"duration":2.4}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct, Your Honor and it was -- the hair was delivered to the crime laboratory on the 28th.","start":801.474,"stop":809.164,"duration":7.69}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then how do you jump to the conclusion that between the 28th and 30th that it had been discovered it was not a hair from his body and the interrogating officers knew it?","start":809.164,"stop":818.222,"duration":9.06},{"text":"How do you --","start":818.222,"stop":818.623,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"All we can say on that, Your Honor, is that either they knew it or that they made a statement to the petitioner with this regard whether it was true or false.","start":818.623,"stop":831.429,"duration":12.81},{"text":"Now, we say it doesn't make any difference whether they knew it or whether they -- they told it to him without making the determination.","start":831.429,"stop":840.195,"duration":8.77}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, on this branch of your case, are you making two points -- one that the police used the hair to get the confession and that that was error?","start":840.195,"stop":852.142,"duration":11.95}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice Fortas.","start":852.142,"stop":852.944,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And two that there was error before the prosecution to fail to advice the counsel?","start":852.944,"stop":862.037,"duration":9.09}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":862.037,"stop":862.233,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- or the petitioner that their expert had reported that the hairs were the same?","start":862.233,"stop":868.38,"duration":6.15}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":868.38,"stop":869.059,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- or not the same?","start":869.059,"stop":870.303,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct.","start":870.303,"stop":870.834,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"So you have those two points?","start":870.834,"stop":872.277,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct.","start":872.277,"stop":873.125,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What did counsel do about this when -- on it, wherein from the petitioner that he had told the interrogators it wasn't his hair?","start":873.125,"stop":882.867,"duration":9.74}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The record is silent on that.","start":882.867,"stop":885.322,"duration":2.46},{"text":"Now, of course they --","start":885.322,"stop":886.506,"duration":1.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does that mean they did nothing?","start":886.506,"stop":891.446,"duration":4.94}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"The record doesn't show that they did anything.","start":891.446,"stop":894.169,"duration":2.72},{"text":"But of course they were in a terrible position because what could they do is see that the state never introduced the hair at the trial.","start":894.169,"stop":905.079,"duration":10.91}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, this -- it would seem to me that if it was a valuable evidence for -- for the defendant now, in this proceeding, it's certainly would have been valuable evidence to him then and if counsel was taking cognizance of what would help him, he would think they would make some kind of an effort to have it determined.","start":905.079,"stop":928.901,"duration":23.82},{"text":"There's a fact --","start":928.901,"stop":929.338,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"And if --","start":929.338,"stop":930.084,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- whether it was his or not?","start":930.084,"stop":931.607,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, all they had was what this uneducated cab driver with a two-year high school education at the most told them, he told the investigating authority --","start":931.607,"stop":946.084,"duration":14.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's why they have lawyers with more two years education and to take care of his rights in the courtroom that would think.","start":946.084,"stop":954.352,"duration":8.27}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, and that -- that is the reason that they made the -- the request, to have -- to be permitted to make a scientific examination of the evidence and that was denied.","start":954.352,"stop":967.478,"duration":13.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they -- did they state why they wanted to do that?","start":967.478,"stop":972.388,"duration":4.91}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":972.388,"stop":972.741,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they say it to him it was because the defendant said that was not his hair and that they wanted to examine that particular item of evidence?","start":972.741,"stop":982.996,"duration":10.25}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No, the motion does not state that.","start":982.996,"stop":986.39,"duration":3.39},{"text":"It does not, no.","start":986.39,"stop":988.951,"duration":2.56},{"text":"Now --","start":988.951,"stop":989.742,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it refer that the hair, the vial was distinguished in other physical --","start":989.742,"stop":993.674,"duration":3.93},{"text":"No, it does not.","start":993.674,"stop":995.561,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"It does not, Mr. Justice Harlan.","start":995.561,"stop":997.98,"duration":2.42},{"text":"Now --","start":997.98,"stop":998.989,"duration":1.01}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Just one last on that question.","start":998.989,"stop":1001.103,"duration":2.11},{"text":"Did these lawyers testify at the least the post-conviction or other proceedings?","start":1001.103,"stop":1005.196,"duration":4.09}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, they did.","start":1005.196,"stop":1006.123,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they -- did they testify that the motion itself didn't say anything about it?","start":1006.123,"stop":1011.784,"duration":5.66},{"text":"What it was -- they had in mind when they made the motion?","start":1011.784,"stop":1015.543,"duration":3.76}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe they did and I -- I'm not certain about that but I don't think they did.","start":1015.543,"stop":1019.999,"duration":4.46}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in any event, they certainly didn't say they had in mind they wanted an examination of the hair, did they?","start":1019.999,"stop":1024.816,"duration":4.82}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe they did.","start":1024.816,"stop":1025.906,"duration":1.09},{"text":"I am not certain of what of state of the record is on that point.","start":1025.906,"stop":1029.814,"duration":3.91},{"text":"Now, the -- then the -- then the next step was there was a habeas corpus proceeding in the Northern District of Illinois, relief was denied and that was affirmed by the Supreme -- by the Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit and that was held up by the other counsel.","start":1029.814,"stop":1050.387,"duration":20.57},{"text":"Then, we came to August of 1963 when a petition for commutation was filed and the -- there was a hearing before the Illinois Pardon and Parole Board and in the course of that hearing there was certain evidence introduced by the prosecution and by the defendants which -- which for the first time cast substantial real doubt on the man's guilt and the -- we were then about two days before the execution, the execution was set for one minute after midnight on August the 23rd and the commutation was denied on August the 20th.","start":1050.387,"stop":1100.516,"duration":50.13},{"text":"So we proceeded in two channels.","start":1100.516,"stop":1104.285,"duration":3.77},{"text":"One was, the date for death that have been sent by the Supreme Court of Illinois which was not been in session --","start":1104.285,"stop":1111.066,"duration":6.78}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"When -- when does he have counsel for the first time?","start":1111.066,"stop":1119.05,"duration":7.98}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"His parents obtained counsel for him even while he was still being interrogated.","start":1119.05,"stop":1126.217,"duration":7.17}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, before he signed the confession?","start":1126.217,"stop":1128.707,"duration":2.49}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, that's true.","start":1128.707,"stop":1129.539,"duration":0.83},{"text":"The counsel never saw him until after the confession was signed.","start":1129.539,"stop":1132.781,"duration":3.24}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Why -- why not?","start":1132.781,"stop":1135.74,"duration":2.96}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"They -- he was held incommunicado.","start":1135.74,"stop":1138.408,"duration":2.67},{"text":"He asked to see --","start":1138.408,"stop":1138.615,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, (Voice Overlap) refused to let him see him?","start":1138.615,"stop":1140.658,"duration":2.04}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct and --","start":1140.658,"stop":1142.543,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But the lawyer tried to see him?","start":1142.543,"stop":1146.584,"duration":4.04}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe the record shows that his lawyer inquiries to get to see him and I believe that the -- the first time that his lawyers saw him was on December the 1st which was the morning following the night when he signed the confession.","start":1146.584,"stop":1162.415,"duration":15.83}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did I ask you before we adjourned if the doctor who made this -- this test of the material in the -- in the vial testified --","start":1162.415,"stop":1175.376,"duration":12.96}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He did --","start":1175.376,"stop":1175.419,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in the case?","start":1175.419,"stop":1176.164,"duration":0.74}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He did testify, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":1176.164,"stop":1178.352,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did -- did he say anything about the hair being attached to --","start":1178.352,"stop":1183.431,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he did not.","start":1183.431,"stop":1184.749,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was he asked by counsel from cross-examination whether there was any such thing in the vial?","start":1184.749,"stop":1191.856,"duration":7.11}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"He -- there was nothing.","start":1191.856,"stop":1193.924,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"No mention of it by --","start":1193.924,"stop":1194.748,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"No mentioned --","start":1194.748,"stop":1195.35,"duration":0.6}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- by either side?","start":1195.35,"stop":1196.493,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Willard J. Lassers","textObjs":[{"text":"By either side, that is correct.","start":1196.493,"stop":1198.376,"duration":1.88},{"text":"Yes, I believe he testified that the injury were something about the character.","start":1198.376,"stop":1203.428,"duration":5.05},{"text":"So that was the -- we made an application to a justice of the Supreme Court of Illinois in vacation, for a stay, that was denied.","start":1203.428,"stop":1214.519,"duration":11.09},{"text":"We filed a second application for habeas corpus which was the time when the present group of attorneys accepted the case and that was granted by Judge Decker and then the matter was sat down for a full hearing before Judge Perry.","start":1214.519,"stop":1228.916,"duration":14.4},{"text":"And --","start":1228.916,"stop":1229.077,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll recess -- we'll recess now Mister.","start":1229.077,"stop":1233.56,"duration":4.48}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Jan  11 - 12, 1967","petitioner":"Miller","respondent":"Pate","docket":"250","citation":"386 US 1 (1967)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/386/1","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Feb 13, 1967"}